1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:01,960
I told you to stay in this mansion!

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:03,560
Why did you come?

3
00:00:03,960 --> 00:00:05,480
What if something happened to you?

4
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:06,880
What would I do?

5
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:09,360
If I hadn’t arrived, you would have become
a killer!

6
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:12,160
You would have gone to
prison as a bloody murderer!

7
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:16,200
Lately, I keep seeing Murat in my dreaMrs.

8
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:18,640
It seems
like he has no peace where he lies.

9
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:21,680
Whatever came upon us,
it was because of that boy.

10
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:24,040
Don’t ever speak a word about Murat again.

11
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,640
Enough already.

12
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,880
Know the
truth and stop being so close to the fire.

13
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:31,640
Murat isn’t our son, Nermin.

14
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:33,760
He’s someone else’s child.

15
00:00:34,360 --> 00:00:36,960
No, this can’t be true!

16
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:39,280
If you don’t believe me, go ask Binnaz.

17
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,400
Murat isn’t my son?

18
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:43,640
Forgive me, Mrs. Nermin.

19
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:51,320
I swear, I honestly didn’t know Murat was
Mrs. Müzeyyen’s son.

20
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:55,840
You killed my Murat, the
child you gave birth to.

21
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:00,080
You did it with your own hands.

22
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,600
You saw with your own eyes that he died!

23
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:08,360
Mom, such a thing can’t be a lie!

24
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:14,040
Anyone who doesn’t believe
it, or wants to question it, go to Haydar!

25
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:16,440
You gave birth on the same day as Nermin.

26
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,720
Our boy didn’t survive.

27
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:22,216
But when I saw your baby,
I took him and brought him to the mansion.

28
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,240
That’s it.

29
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,280
Haydar!

30
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,480
With these hands, I handed over the weapon.

31
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,720
With these hands, I killed my son.

32
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,680
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

33
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,999
Even
if my hands burned, it wouldn’t be enough.

34
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,160
Even if
they were cut off, it wouldn’t be enough.

35
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,800
I buried my child.

36
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:45,000
I buried him a second time.

37
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,480
I caused it to my child.

38
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,800
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

39
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:59,120
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

40
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,959
And now we reach the end.

41
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:03,879
This isn't something to watch alone.

42
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:06,199
This is something we experience together.

43
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:11,760
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

44
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:15,320
They will premiere
on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

45
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,839
One moment.

46
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,719
One story. One ending.

47
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:22,279
So grab your comfy blanket and a
huge bucket

48
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:25,280
of popcorn for one final twist.

49
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,360
Let's be there together.

50
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:17,600
[MERCAN HUMMING SONG]

51
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,600
What do you want?

52
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,040
Was there something?

53
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,320
Today is Tahir’s birthday.

54
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,960
I came to tell you that.

55
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,920
Maybe you don’t know.

56
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,360
Thank you.

57
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:08,800
Murat... my
brother... I didn’t recognize him at all.

58
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,160
We were like
two strangers in the same mansion.

59
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:18,000
I don’t know anything about him.

60
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,440
I want to get to know my brother.

61
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,120
If the memories about
him hadn’t been burned...

62
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:36,600
maybe I could have given you something.

63
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,960
But all that remains are just the photos.

64
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,640
I already gave one to your mother.

65
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,200
I’ll leave the others later.

66
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,920
Mercan, are you okay?

67
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,840
Did Aslı
do something to you? Did she say something?

68
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:15,000
No,
she didn’t do anything. Please stay calm.

69
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:22,640
I should never have let her leave my side.

70
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:26,040
Aslı needs
to leave this mansion immediately.

71
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,560
Let her stay a little longer, please.

72
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:36,040
She wants to get to know Murat. She told me
that.

73
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,640
She can’t do anything to me anyway.

74
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,680
Mercan, Aslı
is dangerous. Don’t forget that.

75
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,400
Okay, I won’t forget.

76
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,280
Let’s drop it now.

77
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,040
Today is a beautiful day.

78
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:58,600
Your
eyes are shining. There’s something in you.

79
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,360
Yes, there is.

80
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,560
Life is strange.

81
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:05,400
On one side, bad things happen...

82
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:09,120
and on the other, beautiful things give
people hope.

83
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,160
And
I want to focus on these beautiful things.

84
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,280
Cemal!

85
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,240
Cemal!

86
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,200
What is it, Mercan?

87
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:44,520
Are you okay?

88
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,480
Oh, I’m tired.

89
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:48,840
What’s wrong?

90
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:54,200
Well, today is Ateş’s,
I mean Tahir’s birthday.

91
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,480
Mom!

92
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:59,080
How could I forget that?
And we even call him brother, God damn it.

93
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,840
How did you find out?

94
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:04,240
Aslı told me. I didn’t know at all.

95
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,640
Our Aslı?

96
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,760
Yes.

97
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,600
Don’t ask, I’m very surprised too.

98
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,840
But anyway, we’ll talk about this later.

99
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,040
Right now, I need your help.

100
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,480
Sure, whatever you say.

101
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,040
So, the village...

102
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:29,040
I wonder what you’re
up to again, little water fairy.

103
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:41,960
Bir fırtına tuttu bizi.

104
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:47,080
Derya yakardı.

105
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:59,760
O bizim kavuşmalarımız
yarim... mahşere kaldı.

106
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:13,720
O bizim kavuşmalarımız
yarim... mahşere kaldı.

107
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:21,720
O bizim kavuşmalarımız
yarim... mahşere kaldı.

108
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:29,800
Really, if you have no requests from Malik,

109
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,720
you’ll sign this marriage contract.

110
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:47,920
My Çiçek?

111
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,880
Are you okay? What happened?

112
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:55,880
Nothing,
I just shivered suddenly. Nothing’s wrong.

113
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:02,200
Something definitely happened. I
can tell by those looks.

114
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:08,240
I’m sure. If something
happened, I would have told you, right?

115
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,040
Darling, why shouldn’t I be sure?

116
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:16,599
There’s cake. Fresh, I just made it. I’ll
give you some tea on the side.

117
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,759
You drink them.

118
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,760
Çiçek.

119
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Wait.

120
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,840
Did my mother do something again?

121
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:32,920
No. You already know how she is.

122
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,680
I got upset
about what happened. I mean, about my mom.

123
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,720
I just got upset, that’s all.

124
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:44,160
Okay. If that’s how
you feel, I accept it. But don’t be upset.

125
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:47,559
Whatever the problem is,
we’ll solve it together.

126
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,560
Right?

127
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,800
We’ll solve it.

128
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,000
Don’t worry.

129
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:01,720
It’ll pass. It won’t
stay like this forever. Right?

130
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,920
We’ll handle it.

131
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:08,680
Now I had some things to do at the mansion.
Let me take care of them.

132
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:11,600
Then we’ll meet. Okay?

133
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,720
Okay.

134
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:22,960
Oh mom, what did you do this time?

135
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,800
Mom?

136
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,760
How are you?

137
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:49,480
I was going out,
but I wanted to check on you first.

138
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,480
How am I supposed to be? I don’t even know.

139
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:59,800
There’s an emptiness inside me. Feels like
it’s pierced.

140
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:04,680
Always icy, never warms up.

141
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,680
Feels like I buried my brother again.

142
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,520
Mercan, what has your
father made us go through?

143
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,160
I’m very angry.

144
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,680
At myself too.

145
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,800
Murat is my son.

146
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,440
Nothing will change that.

147
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,720
I know.

148
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,000
Same for me. He’s my brother.

149
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,240
I loved him very much.

150
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:46,280
At times, I
ignored you to take care of him.

151
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,640
I did it to save him...

152
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:53,040
Mom, that’s all in the past now.

153
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,200
It’s not past, it’s not over.

154
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:59,640
I burned you to save Murat.

155
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,960
I did that.

156
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:07,640
We never
really had a mother-daughter relationship.

157
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,680
I deprived you of me.

158
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:16,160
But that never meant I didn’t love you.

159
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,040
Know that, okay?

160
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,800
That’s the kind of mother I became.

161
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,720
One cannot bring back the past.

162
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:19,599
What if I hadn’t come?

163
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:24,000
I feel
like I remind everyone of my brother a bit.

164
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:28,520
I told Mercan too, but she never listened.

165
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:30,960
I don’t want to ruin your day.

166
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,760
Mercan didn’t listen to you, huh?

167
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:36,320
She did the right thing. I guess I won’t
listen to you either, just like Mercan.

168
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:39,120
If you don’t want to come with me,
then that’s a different matter.

169
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,240
Where to?

170
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,160
Nowhere, we were just going out for a bit.

171
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:51,080
Mercan was talking to you.

172
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,360
Brother...

173
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,880
She
told me to take Demet out, she’s upset...

174
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,960
let her get some fresh air...

175
00:13:57,120 --> 00:14:01,280
I thought I’d take
care of that. Okay, I’m off. Demet, hop in.

176
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,000
Nothing escapes him either.

177
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:14,000
He suspects even a flying mosquito.

178
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,080
Where to?

179
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:36,840
Not me.

180
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,280
We’re going together.

181
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:39,960
Where are we going?

182
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,480
I don’t know. We’ll just walk around.

183
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,800
I needed a break from home.

184
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,280
If you don’t tell me what’s on your mind...

185
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,840
I’m not responsible for what happens.

186
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,080
Talk.

187
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:04,120
If you want
an answer, you’ll do whatever I say today.

188
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,200
Okay.

189
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:09,920
No questions or anything.

190
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:13,400
Okay. You’re the boss.

191
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:14,920
Whatever you say.

192
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,600
Here you go, sir.

193
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,800
You’re surprising me, madam.

194
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,040
They took my son from me.

195
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:03,320
They took my son from me.

196
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:22,040
Mrs. Müzeyyen, I brought your medicine.

197
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,400
You didn’t kill my son.

198
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,640
Because you killed your own son.

199
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,520
You’re a child murderer.

200
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,560
Murat was the son you thought was dead.

201
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,360
Haydar took him and put him in place of my
dead son.

202
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,680
Mrs. Müzeyyen, I brought your medicine.

203
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,720
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

204
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,960
Okay, Zehra.

205
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,600
You go out, I’ll give her the medicine.

206
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,280
Mom?

207
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,240
Give it, give it.

208
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,000
Leave me alone.

209
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,520
Mom, please don’t do this.

210
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,520
Don’t push me away.

211
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:55,359
He was my brother...

212
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,760
My heart hurts too.

213
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,160
Brother!

214
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,440
They took him from me.

215
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:46,160
They took your brother from us.

216
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,440
Cry, dear mom.

217
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:53,960
Cry.

218
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:57,560
Let it out.

219
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,360
Where should I put it?

220
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:24,720
This seems like a good spot.

221
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:33,840
Like this.

222
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,440
Okay, that looks good.

223
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:41,360
No, that spot isn’t good.

224
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,320
Oh, it’s fine like this.

225
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:46,400
But when
you look, it should catch the eye at first.

226
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:47,640
It won’t work like this.

227
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,440
I went into the room.

228
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,919
The first place I
looked was here, right at the focal point.

229
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,280
Leave it like this, it looks nice.

230
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:56,080
No, let’s put it over here.

231
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:57,800
Okay, let’s put it there.

232
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:06,840
Like this?

233
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,239
No, I changed my mind.

234
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,240
Let’s hang it here.

235
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,600
Here.

236
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:14,360
Okay, let’s hang it there then.

237
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:15,760
That’s what you say.

238
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,240
Wait, no, it didn’t work.

239
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:22,760
Demet, can you make a decision already?

240
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:28,360
But it
won’t work if you do it like this at first.

241
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,440
Okay, I’m hanging it here.

242
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,120
Once I fix this part...

243
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,480
Done, what more do you want?

244
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,560
Look how nice it looks.

245
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:43,160
What else?

246
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:48,880
Do you really believe we’ll do this
on Ateş’s birthday?

247
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,400
What’s the big deal?

248
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:51,919
This is done every birthday.

249
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,920
Demet, what will people say?

250
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:55,840
It doesn’t suit us. Remove it, please.

251
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:00,160
This is how a birthday concept works, dear.

252
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:01,840
God help us.

253
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:03,296
Don’t honk this, give it here.

254
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:03,920
No.

255
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,040
Don’t honk it now.

256
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:06,120
I said no.

257
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,040
Don’t honk, remove it.

258
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,120
I’m saying no.

259
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,320
I’ll hang these.

260
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,200
I’ll hang this side too.

261
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:00,800
Why did we come here?

262
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:02,760
Wasn’t it no questions?

263
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:05,359
Okay, I’m not asking, but...

264
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,800
There must be a reason.

265
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,960
Forget the reasons for now.

266
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:12,240
I reserved today just for the two of us.

267
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:13,720
Ateş and Mercan.

268
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,400
Just us.

269
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,160
Only the two of us.

270
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,200
This isn’t anything new.

271
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,520
In my world, there’s only you.

272
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,920
Only you.

273
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:30,560
Shall we eat something?

274
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,400
Sure.

275
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,280
Are you in?

276
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:46,920
Loser buys.

277
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,760
Where did these come from?

278
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:00,240
From your childhood.

279
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:23,400
This game doesn’t end like this.

280
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,360
I need to think, Ms. Mercan.

281
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,400
Sorry.

282
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:29,760
I can’t make
a reckless move just because you’re bored.

283
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,080
Oh, don’t do it.

284
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,200
Think for forty hours.

285
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,880
You insist on winning, huh.

286
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,160
You’ve been winning for
how many games already?

287
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,320
So what?

288
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,600
I win fairly with my wrist.

289
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:43,160
You play without thinking.

290
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:45,920
What should I do?

291
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:47,360
I’m bored.

292
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,520
You were like this as a child too.

293
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,480
If you couldn’t win, your face would drop
immediately.

294
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:55,160
Not at all.

295
00:23:56,320 --> 00:23:57,720
Of course, you wouldn’t remember.

296
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,600
Don’t remember when it suits you.

297
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:01,880
You even forgot my name.

298
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,480
I didn’t forget.

299
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,240
Mahir.

300
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:07,800
Kadir.

301
00:24:10,280 --> 00:24:12,040
Tahir, Tahir.

302
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,000
I remember some things, but please.

303
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,880
Like your marbles.

304
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,000
All colorful.

305
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:24,440
I loved looking at them.

306
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:27,920
It
Felt like a magical world was inside them.

307
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,120
Really, what happened to them?

308
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,480
I lost them.

309
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:42,760
Then I grew up.

310
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,520
We’ll get new ones too.

311
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,560
So, did you like it?

312
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:10,640
A lot.

313
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,760
I had a similar one too.

314
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,120
I used to play with it.

315
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,880
I mean, I played with it before.

316
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,000
Are you in then?

317
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:21,800
Are you sure?

318
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:23,520
I’ll play well, watch.

319
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,960
I’m not afraid, you know.

320
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:27,160
I know, I know.

321
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:29,240
But beware.

322
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,080
You’ll lose badly.

323
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:32,920
We’ll see.

324
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,200
Not your chin.

325
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,480
Let your hand work.

326
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:37,560
Give it here.

327
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:38,680
I’ll set them up.

328
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:42,800
Let’s see how good you are.

329
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,960
I want the blue one.

330
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:50,200
That’s nice.
Colorful.

331
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,880
You start first.

332
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,320
What happened?

333
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:07,760
How do I play?

334
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,160
Weren’t you the one who wanted to play?

335
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:17,440
Okay.

336
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,640
Squat down slowly.

337
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,280
Look.

338
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:25,920
The marble
will be between your thumb and this finger.

339
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:32,080
Then choose a target and
flick it toward the target.

340
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:34,440
Like this?

341
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:35,840
Yes.

342
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:44,920
That doesn’t count though.

343
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,800
That wasn’t the first try.

344
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,480
Step aside.

345
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,000
Did you see?

346
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:17,680
But you stretched your hand too far.

347
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,160
Look, I threw it from here.

348
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:22,720
Look, if you’re going to be fussy, we won’t
play at all.

349
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,520
I’m not being fussy, sir.

350
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:27,320
If I threw it
from here, you’ll throw it from here too.

351
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,960
I threw it from
there, but if you want, I’ll hit from here.

352
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,680
See, you missed.

353
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:00,120
Where?

354
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,640
Here, here.

355
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:09,400
Thank you.

356
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:22,880
Now come on.

357
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:34,520
Did you see?

358
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,320
Winning makes it more enjoyable to eat.

359
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,560
Enjoy.

360
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,680
Beginner’s luck.

361
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,200
Sometimes not knowing
allows you to act fearlessly.

362
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:10,360
This isn’t beginner’s luck, it’s courage,
you understand?

363
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:13,880
Where do you learn such things?

364
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,200
I know these things.

365
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,200
You know, you know.

366
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,560
You know everything anyway.

367
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:26,920
Are you in?

368
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,200
In what?

369
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:31,160
Come with me.

370
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:32,760
Where?

371
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:10,200
Why do you have this?

372
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:13,320
Give it to me, give me my son.

373
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,560
Let me know my son.

374
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:23,640
What do you want to learn, huh?

375
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:26,400
He was failing at school.

376
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:29,920
He would get beaten by his father for it.

377
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:36,720
He would immediately come
and seek refuge with me.

378
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:38,480
Because I didn’t care.

379
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,000
Is that what you want to learn?

380
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,920
You learned it.

381
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,320
Anything else?

382
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,480
Do you know which food he loved most?

383
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:55,400
Stuffed eggplant.

384
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:57,760
Dessert was revani.

385
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:00,720
He adored revani.

386
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,960
But now he can’t eat it.

387
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:08,120
Why?

388
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,920
Because you killed him.

389
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:21,400
He loved cats a lot.

390
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:24,560
He had a cat.

391
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,120
He cried a lot when it died.

392
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:34,120
He loved cats.

393
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:35,880
He was allergic to pistachios.

394
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,120
What else do you want to learn?

395
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,720
What good will it do you once you learn?

396
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,640
You won’t have memories with him.

397
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:48,160
You won’t have a single memory.

398
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,920
Because his mother is me.

399
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:57,880
Not you.

400
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,560
You burned the last memories left from him.

401
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,960
You burned them.

402
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:11,760
Your husband took him from me.

403
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:16,760
You also killed my son.

404
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:20,080
You two are no different from each other.

405
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:23,160
You’re both murderers.

406
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:29,800
His mother is me, me! Not you.

407
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:31,640
You are his murderer.

408
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,000
I didn’t kill him.

409
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,720
I didn’t kill my son.

410
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,320
Which mother would harm her child?

411
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,680
If I had known he was alive...

412
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:47,600
I would have embraced him.

413
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:49,520
You make me sick.

414
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,440
Give him to me, let go.

415
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,520
Leave him.

416
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,840
I’ll never give him to you.

417
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,280
You couldn’t protect your son.

418
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,440
What good would keeping his photo do?

419
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:12,560
I wish you had protected him.

420
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:16,000
I wish you had protected him so he’d live.

421
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:18,600
True.

422
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:20,200
You speak the truth.

423
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,680
I wish I had protected my son from you.

424
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:28,880
From your hatred.

425
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:34,400
I wish I had protected
my son from your filthy hands.

426
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,400
I’ll hold
accountable each of those who separated us.

427
00:33:57,640 --> 00:34:00,319
Whoever shares Haydar’s blood...

428
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,720
will taste death from my hand.

429
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,240
I promise you.

430
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:07,320
I promise.

431
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:19,600
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

432
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:22,920
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

433
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,759
And now we reach the end.

434
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,679
This isn't something to watch alone.

435
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:29,999
This is something we experience together.

436
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:35,560
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

437
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:39,120
They will premiere
on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

438
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:40,639
One moment.

439
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:43,519
One story. One ending.

440
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:46,079
So grab your comfy blanket and a
huge bucket

441
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:49,080
of popcorn for one final twist.

442
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:51,160
Let's be there together.

443
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,240
Look at the state Haydar
Yıldırım has fallen into.

444
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:19,080
Where are you going, old man?

445
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:22,760
Let me pass.

446
00:35:22,761 --> 00:35:24,400
I don’t want any trouble.

447
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,760
He doesn’t want trouble. Did you hear?

448
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,200
I heard.

449
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:33,160
Brother, I didn’t do anything to you, step
aside.

450
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,360
But you did to someone else.

451
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:39,280
What’s happening, man?

452
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:43,480
We’ll make a small hole in your stomach.

453
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:48,600
Müzeyyen sent you, right?

454
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:51,279
I’ll give you more, double the money.

455
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,960
Your money won’t work on us.

456
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:11,280
You guessed right.

457
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:13,400
I
Brought you some salami from Mrs. Müzeyyen.

458
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:46,880
My dear.

459
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,320
My husband.

460
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:49,520
Good luck.

461
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:50,680
Thank you.

462
00:36:51,200 --> 00:36:52,440
What have you done? Let me see.

463
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:54,360
I made börek, brewed tea.

464
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,480
You brewed tea, made börek.

465
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:02,640
Then put some tea so we
can drink it together.

466
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:04,920
Okay, sure. You sit first.

467
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:06,400
Should I sit?

468
00:37:06,401 --> 00:37:08,760
Sit and relax, I’ll bring it to you.

469
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:09,880
Let me rest.

470
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:14,720
Of course, dear.

471
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:19,120
My dear, you might think of me as...

472
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:21,640
Like I’m sick.

473
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:23,640
Put everything beside you.

474
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:29,160
Cake, baklava, dessert, savory,
crackers, whatever, just everything.

475
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:31,560
I’ll eat everything.

476
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:35,600
My dear, right now I feel like a king.

477
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,720
Everything is mine.

478
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:40,120
Coffee table?

479
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:41,480
I’ll bring it right away.

480
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:45,240
Sorry to keep you waiting.

481
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:47,680
Oh my, oh my.

482
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,480
Wow, it looks really nice.

483
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:54,400
My dear, what happened?

484
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:56,120
Zehra, what happened?

485
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:57,760
What happened?

486
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,240
My God.

487
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:03,040
My dear, what happened?

488
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,720
Are you okay, my dear?

489
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:10,920
My God, what suddenly happened to her?

490
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,480
My dear, what happened?

491
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:19,360
Come, come, come, come, come, come.

492
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:21,360
Come, sweetheart, sit.

493
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:22,920
Sit.

494
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,120
Oh, let’s put this behind you too.

495
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:26,920
My dear, are you okay?

496
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,640
What happened, exactly?

497
00:38:30,600 --> 00:38:32,800
Do you want
anything? There’s salty, crackers, börek.

498
00:38:33,080 --> 00:38:34,760
Berat, for God’s sake.

499
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:37,160
Stop talking about food.

500
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:39,080
Can you control your throat now?

501
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,720
You upset my stomach for no reason.

502
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,360
I’ll take this away.

503
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:45,440
Okay.

504
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:46,800
Done.

505
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,280
Okay, come, come.

506
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:49,880
My dear, are you okay?

507
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:52,240
What suddenly happened to you like this?

508
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:56,440
You know baklava, cake,
desserts are part of my daily routine.

509
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,680
Berat, for God’s sake.

510
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,280
I will say God’s name, be quiet.

511
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:05,680
You’re okay, right, my dear?

512
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:07,600
I’m fine, I’m fine.

513
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:13,960
Zehra, should we see a doctor, God
forbid nothing serious turns up?

514
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:16,840
Berat, can you get me a glass of water?

515
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:20,280
Water? I’ll get it right away. Wait.

516
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:21,880
What happened?

517
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,040
My God.

518
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:28,720
Now it’s on my mind too.

519
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:33,600
Drink, drink, drink.

520
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:37,039
Look, my dear.

521
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:39,080
Don’t insist, come on, let’s go.

522
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:43,600
Or else? No, nothing.

523
00:39:44,240 --> 00:39:45,240
Impossible, it isn’t.

524
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,680
No need, Berat, I’m fine.

525
00:39:49,240 --> 00:39:50,240
You’re fine.

526
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:55,600
Can you keep up?

527
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,000
I can’t keep up.

528
00:39:58,600 --> 00:39:59,840
Mercan, enough now, come on.

529
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:02,280
I can’t keep up.

530
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,560
Let’s go already, we’ll get caught.

531
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,736
I’ll get it from the market for you, come
on.

532
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:09,280
No, it won’t be enjoyable that way.

533
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:10,800
Weren’t I the boss today?

534
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:16,840
You’re always the boss, so where did this
energy come from today?

535
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:20,560
Come on, we’ll get caught, let’s go.

536
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,280
Don’t argue, go a bit higher. I can’t keep
up.

537
00:40:24,600 --> 00:40:25,600
That’s enough already.

538
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:41,160
What are you doing? Why did you lower me?

539
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:43,320
My shoulder’s killing me.

540
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:46,600
Feels unfair, as if I’m overweight.

541
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:49,600
Honestly, I don’t know,
my shoulders rebelled.

542
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,840
Fine then, I’ll climb too.

543
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:17,200
Look... Still calling
it a tree, like a cat.

544
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:21,920
Where did all this energy come from,
I don’t understand. Come on, walk.

545
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:23,440
We’ll get caught, Mercan.

546
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:26,200
Nothing will happen, if
we get caught, we get caught, so what?

547
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:32,920
You insisted. Okay,
stop. Stop, go down. I’ll go up.

548
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:35,400
Who’s there?

549
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,880
Mercan?

550
00:41:43,440 --> 00:41:45,560
Mercan, again you?

551
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,560
You’ve grown up but you’re still the same.

552
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,000
Did she recognize you?

553
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:04,880
Yes, but she’s very
sweet. She’ll see, but won’t say anything.

554
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:07,160
Don’t worry, it’s fine.

555
00:42:08,200 --> 00:42:09,680
So why did we do it secretly then?

556
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:15,960
For you... to
make it exciting, so you’d experience it.

557
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:23,760
I don’t think you’ve
ever done such a thing. You haven’t, right?

558
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:29,160
I had already realized the story
you told was made up.

559
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,320
My wife understands everything.

560
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:41,680
So you told that story just to cheer me up.

561
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:46,120
I know you so well. But admit it, you liked
it.

562
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:49,560
I brought excitement into our lives.

563
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,720
Maybe a bit too much excitement?

564
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,840
Shall we head back?

565
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:01,760
No, today isn’t over yet, Ateş Karahan.

566
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:07,560
We have a lot of craziness to do. In fact,
one is waiting in the car trunk.

567
00:43:08,520 --> 00:43:09,520
In the trunk?

568
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:21,600
A kite?

569
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:34,320
We’ll
do everything we left unfinished, together.

570
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:55,160
Tahir! Tahir!

571
00:43:58,800 --> 00:43:59,800
Where’s Eylül?

572
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:02,080
Sick, sleeping.

573
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:13,600
What’s this?

574
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:18,640
A
Kite. One day we’ll fly it too if you want.

575
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:27,440
I
Want to, make it colorful. Just like this.

576
00:44:28,440 --> 00:44:29,520
I’ll make it for you too.

577
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:46,080
Mercan, quickly home.

578
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:50,080
My father’s calling, I’m going.

579
00:45:05,040 --> 00:45:06,320
I’ve never flown a kite.

580
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:07,960
Neither have I.

581
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,560
We’ll do a first together.

582
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:17,200
Everyone should have a kite in the sky.

583
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,320
Then let’s go.

584
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:33,120
You stay here. Give it to me.

585
00:45:45,800 --> 00:45:46,800
Ready?

586
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:54,840
One, two, three.

587
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:12,960
Hold.

588
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:57,320
I brought your tea.

589
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,920
I made myself a coffee too.

590
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:02,600
We’re tired, really.

591
00:47:02,960 --> 00:47:04,840
Once
I sit, I feel like drinking something too.

592
00:47:05,440 --> 00:47:07,480
All day,
even if I fought a man, I’d be this tired.

593
00:47:08,360 --> 00:47:11,040
Cemal, I
don’t know what you compared it to.

594
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:15,160
I said the first thing that came
to mind. Why are you making an issue of it?

595
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:21,880
Looks nice. Well done.

596
00:47:22,720 --> 00:47:24,840
We’re tired, but it was worth it.

597
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:29,080
It was worth it. Ateş will
be very surprised to see what we’ve done.

598
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:33,080
Obviously, hard things
have happened lately.

599
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:35,560
They deserve it, they need it.

600
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:45,880
By lately, I mean birthdays, special
occasions, I said it for celebration purposes.

601
00:47:47,400 --> 00:47:48,760
When was your birthday, Demet?

602
00:47:50,520 --> 00:47:53,720
So if you’re planning a special surprise,
it’s unnecessary.

603
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:57,000
We could
just take you to a kebab place. Let it be.

604
00:47:58,400 --> 00:48:00,880
Well, if it’s my birthday, I’d
want something special.

605
00:48:01,560 --> 00:48:02,560
Like sushi, for example.

606
00:48:03,640 --> 00:48:06,320
No, Demet, I won’t get sushi. I gave it a
chance, but no.

607
00:48:06,560 --> 00:48:09,920
We couldn’t connect with it. No
need to force it now.

608
00:48:10,680 --> 00:48:15,160
Let it be. On one’s birthday, even raw fish
is eaten for me.

609
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:36,560
The tea is hot too. But
tea is always hot anyway.

610
00:48:58,560 --> 00:48:59,560
You eat, go ahead.

611
00:49:00,320 --> 00:49:02,040
No, I’m on a diet.

612
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:06,280
Demet, do you have something diet-friendly?
You’re skin and bones already, eat.

613
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:07,736
That’s enough for both of us anyway.

614
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:08,960
Then I’ll take it.

615
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:12,600
But you also eat one for me.

616
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:15,920
This isn’t like the sushi you brought me,
right?

617
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:18,120
No.

618
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:43,600
It was a very nice day.

619
00:49:44,400 --> 00:49:45,400
Very.

620
00:49:46,320 --> 00:49:47,440
You wish it would never end.

621
00:49:56,120 --> 00:49:57,280
Then let it not end.

622
00:50:16,560 --> 00:50:18,440
What else are we doing?

623
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:20,880
Do you have something in mind?

624
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:28,240
Actually, yes.

625
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:35,280
What are you doing, get up.

626
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:38,000
Ateş.

627
00:50:38,800 --> 00:50:41,640
I watched it in a movie.

628
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:43,640
I know that movie.

629
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:53,720
Come on.

630
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:07,680
Whatever we do from now on, together.

631
00:51:08,960 --> 00:51:09,960
No separations.

632
00:51:11,320 --> 00:51:16,040
Today I realized I wasn’t a child at all.

633
00:51:19,120 --> 00:51:24,760
Revenge and hatred take all the good
feelings from a person’s heart.

634
00:51:31,240 --> 00:51:32,240
Our childhood too.

635
00:51:40,720 --> 00:51:43,840
Today you gave me the
childhood I never had.

636
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:47,000
Not just happy memories.

637
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:50,840
You left a big sun in my heart.

638
00:51:52,520 --> 00:51:54,720
Enough of having to grow up all this time.

639
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:57,840
Now it’s time to be each other’s playmates.

640
00:52:03,760 --> 00:52:07,360
Whatever we wanted to
do but couldn’t, we’ll do together.

641
00:52:15,480 --> 00:52:23,480
Sometimes holding someone’s hand eases the pain
of someone who never held a hand as a child.

642
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:37,840
Never let go of my hand.

643
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:40,720
I have no intention of letting go.

644
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:09,880
Just like in that movie.

645
00:53:12,600 --> 00:53:15,240
Now we need to dance too.

646
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:18,000
So it’s complete then.

647
00:53:20,920 --> 00:53:22,800
There’s nothing I can’t do for you.

648
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:41,239
Wait...

649
00:54:41,240 --> 00:54:42,240
Hello.

650
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:53,440
Okay, listen, I don’t want mistakes.
If something goes wrong, I’ll burn you.

651
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:59,080
Come on... Inform me.

652
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:13,000
Nothing is over until
Nezir Keseroğlu says it’s over.

653
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:21,000
All the Karahans will understand, but most
of all Ateş.

654
00:55:24,440 --> 00:55:28,000
Damn, boy... I’ll
make you regret the day you recognized me.

655
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:06,800
If you’re looking for
Malik, he’s gone out... He’ll be here soon.

656
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:15,600
No, I came for you. You’ve
thought about what I said, right?

657
00:56:16,880 --> 00:56:18,600
I thought, of course I thought.

658
00:56:41,960 --> 00:56:43,880
Actually, there wasn’t much to think about.

659
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:47,360
I’m
not after money and wealth like you think.

660
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:55,840
As long as Malik is happy, that’s enough for me.
Having him by my side is the greatest treasure for me.

661
00:56:56,600 --> 00:56:57,640
The right decision.

662
00:56:59,160 --> 00:57:01,960
Not for you, this is right for me.

663
00:57:03,440 --> 00:57:07,160
There are things in life more important
than money, but you’ve forgotten them.

664
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:09,000
Like what?

665
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:17,960
Honor, dignity, morality, pride,
for example.

666
00:57:24,760 --> 00:57:26,120
What’s happening here?

667
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:33,200
Nothing. We were just talking to him.

668
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:39,440
We talked while waiting for you.

669
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:41,720
Is that so?

670
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:45,400
Let’s see if that’s true.

671
00:58:00,760 --> 00:58:02,360
Did you do this too?

672
00:58:03,440 --> 00:58:06,000
I mean,
every time I think, what else could he do.

673
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:08,640
But every time, you manage to surprise me,
mother.

674
00:58:12,040 --> 00:58:13,040
Malik.

675
00:58:13,720 --> 00:58:15,160
Çiçek...

676
00:58:20,720 --> 00:58:22,600
There’s only one promise
between me and Çiçek.

677
00:58:24,440 --> 00:58:29,360
That’s
the promise to be together for a lifetime.

678
00:58:35,360 --> 00:58:37,840
Understand this already, okay?

679
00:59:06,440 --> 00:59:07,440
Are you tired?

680
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:12,760
Today was such a beautiful day, I
want to engrave it in my memory.

681
00:59:14,320 --> 00:59:15,600
Me too.

682
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:19,040
Did you have fun?

683
00:59:20,120 --> 00:59:21,120
A lot.

684
00:59:26,520 --> 00:59:29,200
Your smile is my favorite view.

685
00:59:30,640 --> 00:59:31,640
It does me a lot of good.

686
00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:35,800
Being able to make you feel good is
the greatest kindness I can do for myself.

687
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:41,160
Thank you.

688
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:50,680
For today, for your love,
for your presence, for everything.

689
00:59:55,480 --> 00:59:57,320
I don’t want to go back to the mansion at
all.

690
00:59:57,840 --> 00:59:59,040
As you wish.

691
01:00:00,880 --> 01:00:01,880
Let’s not go back.

692
01:00:02,400 --> 01:00:04,120
Let’s not go back... Where shall we go?

693
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:07,720
I think you know well where I want to go.

694
01:00:07,840 --> 01:00:09,120
You have only one guess.

695
01:00:12,680 --> 01:00:13,680
Ready?

696
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:16,880
Let’s see.

697
01:00:59,160 --> 01:01:00,160
Yes, sir?

698
01:01:00,920 --> 01:01:03,280
Haydar didn’t
die, he was taken to the hospital injured.

699
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:07,600
Incompetent men.

700
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:09,240
How is his condition?

701
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:11,120
I don’t know yet.

702
01:01:12,200 --> 01:01:14,360
I’m in
front of the hospital, I’ll find out soon.

703
01:01:14,920 --> 01:01:18,000
Haydar won’t make it out of that hospital.
Do you hear me?

704
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:20,080
Okay, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

705
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:40,480
I won’t have peace until you die, Haydar.

706
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:25,360
Mother, nothing’s wrong, right? You called
us urgently to talk or something.

707
01:02:27,040 --> 01:02:32,120
Son, wait a little. I’ll say it anyway, let
Çiçek’s group come first.

708
01:02:37,280 --> 01:02:38,280
I’m fine, okay.

709
01:02:43,120 --> 01:02:45,120
Mother, you’re scaring me.

710
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:46,960
You’re okay, right?

711
01:02:47,960 --> 01:02:50,400
Daughter, I told you I’m fine. I’m fine.

712
01:02:53,280 --> 01:02:56,080
You’ll be fine of course, mother. You’re
fine.

713
01:02:58,280 --> 01:03:00,080
I mean, what’s done is done, mother.

714
01:03:00,240 --> 01:03:01,640
It’s not your fault.

715
01:03:06,280 --> 01:03:09,520
Who has been able to handle Haydar? And you
will?

716
01:03:12,640 --> 01:03:14,960
I think we should close
this topic now, right?

717
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:26,160
It’s over, gone.

718
01:03:28,280 --> 01:03:30,920
Oh,
there was so much to do, but I handled it.

719
01:03:31,800 --> 01:03:33,440
I got through everything.

720
01:03:34,000 --> 01:03:35,000
Good evening.

721
01:03:35,760 --> 01:03:36,760
Welcome, brother.

722
01:03:37,240 --> 01:03:39,240
Thank you.

723
01:03:44,400 --> 01:03:48,680
Since
you’re here, I’ll say what I need to say.

724
01:03:49,160 --> 01:03:50,320
Listen to me.

725
01:03:57,200 --> 01:04:05,200
After all that’s happened, I no longer have
the face to look anyone in the eye.

726
01:04:10,240 --> 01:04:12,240
I have no face, that is.

727
01:04:18,960 --> 01:04:20,640
This burden is heavy on me.

728
01:04:31,520 --> 01:04:36,640
That’s
why I’ve decided to request my retirement.

729
01:05:20,960 --> 01:05:23,160
You carry the bags, I’m very tired.

730
01:05:25,960 --> 01:05:27,960
You
could’ve taken a few of the bags at least.

731
01:05:29,280 --> 01:05:31,520
You’ll
handle it, your strong arms can carry them.

732
01:05:34,400 --> 01:05:37,240
Women don’t do this,
don’t do that when it doesn’t suit them.

733
01:05:37,880 --> 01:05:38,880
What about equality?

734
01:05:54,560 --> 01:05:56,080
Look how much shopping they did.

735
01:06:11,120 --> 01:06:13,240
Look how much shopping you did.

736
01:06:13,680 --> 01:06:14,920
You go ahead, I’ll manage.

737
01:06:16,480 --> 01:06:17,760
Light the stove, I’m coming now.

738
01:07:08,360 --> 01:07:10,000
Who are you?

739
01:07:11,160 --> 01:07:12,200
Are you Nezir’s dog?

740
01:07:13,160 --> 01:07:14,160
Speak.

741
01:07:14,240 --> 01:07:15,320
Who’s your master, tell me!

742
01:07:15,640 --> 01:07:17,360
I don’t have a master, really.

743
01:07:17,680 --> 01:07:18,800
I’m a photographer.

744
01:07:19,160 --> 01:07:20,160
I freelance.

745
01:07:28,440 --> 01:07:32,720
Happy birthday, Ateş.

746
01:07:33,040 --> 01:07:36,080
Happy birthday, Ateş.

747
01:07:36,600 --> 01:07:40,000
Happy birthday, happy birthday.

748
01:07:40,200 --> 01:07:43,080
Happy years to you.

749
01:08:47,680 --> 01:08:50,440
You... how did you?

750
01:08:54,160 --> 01:08:54,760
Come on.

751
01:08:55,040 --> 01:08:56,040
We’re in a hurry.

752
01:08:58,840 --> 01:09:00,879
Look, the men are
waiting outside. They’re scouting around.

753
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:02,640
We need to leave before it gets chaotic.

754
01:09:04,560 --> 01:09:05,560
Come on, come on.

755
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:07,640
Your turn, Haydar.

756
01:09:07,960 --> 01:09:09,200
Aren’t you tired of lying down?

757
01:09:10,320 --> 01:09:11,640
How could I be tired?

758
01:09:12,400 --> 01:09:16,520
I live to take revenge
on those who did this to me.

759
01:09:19,360 --> 01:09:20,360
Good.

760
01:09:22,040 --> 01:09:24,440
The opportunity came to
drown Ateş in his own blood.

761
01:09:28,680 --> 01:09:30,160
I’ll take what’s mine.

762
01:09:31,240 --> 01:09:33,520
You’ll send Ateş to the grave too.

763
01:09:39,200 --> 01:09:41,120
Mercan is mine, Ateş will be in the soil.

764
01:09:44,400 --> 01:09:45,400
Come on.

765
01:09:47,280 --> 01:09:48,320
Your turn, Haydar.

766
01:09:50,600 --> 01:09:51,600
Let me get out of here.

767
01:09:52,880 --> 01:09:53,880
The rest is chaos.

768
01:09:55,080 --> 01:09:56,080
Come on.

769
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:06,640
Slow.

770
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:09,840
I’ll make Mercan regret running
from me too.

771
01:10:21,200 --> 01:10:23,520
How
was I to know it would turn out like this?

772
01:10:24,280 --> 01:10:26,640
I had kept him all day to record us.

773
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:30,120
To stay as the mother figure.

774
01:10:30,440 --> 01:10:31,920
That’s why he recorded us all day.

775
01:10:39,440 --> 01:10:40,640
No, the man...

776
01:10:42,320 --> 01:10:44,200
On top of that, he barely
escaped being beaten.

777
01:10:45,560 --> 01:10:47,200
The man was left battered. Poor guy.

778
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:54,200
At least I paid
the hospital expenses generously.

779
01:10:54,240 --> 01:10:56,720
Don’t look at me like
that. I think that counts for something.

780
01:11:05,320 --> 01:11:06,520
But I have to say one thing.

781
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:08,360
You can’t deny the man his due.

782
01:11:08,880 --> 01:11:09,880
He really filmed well.

783
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:17,280
He did his job properly.

784
01:11:35,920 --> 01:11:37,360
Should we have him film us sometime?

785
01:11:38,560 --> 01:11:41,240
If he doesn’t
repent, he’ll probably continue his work.

786
01:11:48,400 --> 01:11:50,520
My God. How would I know?

787
01:11:52,440 --> 01:11:55,400
We wanted to
make a surprise for your birthday.

788
01:12:01,400 --> 01:12:02,680
Today meant this.

789
01:12:07,520 --> 01:12:09,360
That’s why you made me relive my childhood.

790
01:12:20,640 --> 01:12:23,200
I swear, after this hour
I won’t accept excuses.

791
01:12:23,720 --> 01:12:25,960
I’ve been at
it since morning, making these decorations.

792
01:12:29,760 --> 01:12:32,680
Today, this cake will be eaten,
this party will be celebrated. That’s it.

793
01:12:35,120 --> 01:12:36,440
Come on, Demet.

794
01:13:14,200 --> 01:13:15,360
Brother... Haydar ran away.

795
01:13:47,400 --> 01:13:55,160
Happy birthday, Ateş,
happy birthday, Tahir.

796
01:13:56,800 --> 01:14:03,320
Happy birthday, happy birthday, happy years
to you.

797
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:16,200
Happy birthday, my dear love.
I’m glad you exist, glad you’re in my life.

798
01:14:26,160 --> 01:14:27,200
Make a wish.

799
01:14:31,640 --> 01:14:33,280
I have only one wish.

800
01:14:44,320 --> 01:14:45,320
That’s you.

801
01:14:49,640 --> 01:14:52,880
Then let’s blow it out together.

802
01:14:53,840 --> 01:14:57,600
One, two, three.

803
01:15:43,360 --> 01:15:44,680
So, what are you waiting for?

804
01:15:46,480 --> 01:15:47,480
What?

805
01:15:48,080 --> 01:15:49,400
Aren’t you going to cut the cake?

806
01:15:49,960 --> 01:15:50,960
Oh, that’s what you mean.

807
01:15:51,120 --> 01:15:52,880
Of course that’s what I mean.

808
01:15:53,400 --> 01:15:54,400
What’s wrong with you?

809
01:15:55,680 --> 01:15:58,040
You’re here, but your mind seems elsewhere.

810
01:16:02,600 --> 01:16:04,919
In this world where evil roams…

811
01:16:04,920 --> 01:16:08,519
…you are so pure, so delicate…

812
01:16:08,520 --> 01:16:11,880
How could I tell you, in such a happy
moment, that your father escaped from prison?

813
01:16:16,480 --> 01:16:17,839
In my mind, in my heart…

814
01:16:17,840 --> 01:16:19,040
Everything I have is with you.

815
01:16:20,800 --> 01:16:22,160
And it will stay that way forever.

816
01:16:33,760 --> 01:16:34,760
Cemal, will you hold it?

817
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:40,040
My dear love…

818
01:16:40,120 --> 01:16:41,120
My everything.

819
01:17:06,480 --> 01:17:09,520
You are the
most beautiful thing in my life.

820
01:17:10,160 --> 01:17:12,279
From all the bad people…

821
01:17:12,280 --> 01:17:14,759
From all evil…

822
01:17:14,760 --> 01:17:16,960
I will protect you from everything forever.

823
01:17:22,920 --> 01:17:23,920
I know.

824
01:17:25,440 --> 01:17:27,119
You are my hero.

825
01:17:27,120 --> 01:17:29,360
I will never get tired of saying that.

826
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:34,240
And I will make my hero happy until I die.

827
01:17:44,000 --> 01:17:45,640
I’ll cut the cake too.

828
01:17:46,720 --> 01:17:48,280
Come on Demet, let’s cut it downstairs.

829
01:17:48,400 --> 01:17:49,800
Let’s go.

830
01:18:13,120 --> 01:18:16,000
9 millimeter, automatic fire…

831
01:18:16,040 --> 01:18:18,680
One of
the most reliable weapons a man can trust.

832
01:18:20,080 --> 01:18:21,080
Sixteen-round.

833
01:18:21,960 --> 01:18:24,520
Automatic fire, it’s got everything.

834
01:19:19,160 --> 01:19:20,880
No one can find us here, right?

835
01:19:23,400 --> 01:19:24,400
They can’t.

836
01:19:26,000 --> 01:19:27,440
Don’t forget this favor of mine.

837
01:19:30,760 --> 01:19:34,920
When they locked me in the warehouse
before, I asked you to help me escape.

838
01:19:43,760 --> 01:19:45,240
You didn’t help.

839
01:19:46,440 --> 01:19:48,720
What changed now that you helped me escape?

840
01:19:54,280 --> 01:19:55,280
Look at this.

841
01:20:02,200 --> 01:20:03,200
Such a tiny thing.

842
01:20:05,080 --> 01:20:07,000
If you
try to buy it, it’s worth almost nothing.

843
01:20:14,120 --> 01:20:16,640
But its power is greater than its size and
value.

844
01:20:25,280 --> 01:20:27,840
When aimed at the right spot, it can take a
life.

845
01:20:38,520 --> 01:20:40,400
I’ve always found it strange.

846
01:20:42,160 --> 01:20:43,160
Don’t you think so too?

847
01:20:46,600 --> 01:20:48,000
There’s a wedding soon, Haydar.

848
01:20:58,360 --> 01:20:59,720
They didn’t invite me.

849
01:21:01,280 --> 01:21:02,280
Honestly, I was offended.

850
01:21:03,360 --> 01:21:04,640
Did they invite you?

851
01:21:07,720 --> 01:21:09,680
Stop the nonsense and tell me your purpose.

852
01:21:20,120 --> 01:21:21,120
What is this now?

853
01:21:30,200 --> 01:21:31,520
If you’re planning something bad…

854
01:21:34,840 --> 01:21:35,840
Surprise.

855
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:40,240
Go on, Haydar.

856
01:21:42,560 --> 01:21:43,840
It’s time for you to choose.

857
01:21:57,680 --> 01:21:58,880
Go on.

858
01:22:02,040 --> 01:22:04,800
Will you fight with me
or choose your enemy?

859
01:22:16,560 --> 01:22:17,800
Just kidding.

860
01:22:31,120 --> 01:22:33,640
Actually, I don’t like sweets or jokes.

861
01:23:31,080 --> 01:23:32,320
Look at this.

862
01:23:32,760 --> 01:23:34,200
A grown man got scared like that.

863
01:23:52,360 --> 01:23:55,360
How did this man
escape from us? I don’t get it.

864
01:23:55,480 --> 01:23:56,480
How did he manage it?

865
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:08,200
It’s impossible without help.

866
01:24:10,040 --> 01:24:11,600
Let’s increase security at the mansion.

867
01:24:11,800 --> 01:24:12,800
I already handled it.

868
01:24:13,200 --> 01:24:15,520
I sent a message, security has been
increased. No problem.

869
01:24:20,320 --> 01:24:21,520
Won’t you tell Mercan?

870
01:24:24,800 --> 01:24:27,720
Fine, you won’t, but I’ll
tell you this, she’ll figure it out anyway.

871
01:24:29,800 --> 01:24:30,800
I know.

872
01:24:36,760 --> 01:24:37,840
Look at her.

873
01:24:39,640 --> 01:24:41,720
She looks so cheerful.

874
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:52,760
The later she learns, the better.

875
01:24:56,880 --> 01:24:58,560
What are they whispering about?

876
01:24:59,600 --> 01:25:00,600
I wish I knew.

877
01:25:06,960 --> 01:25:07,960
Here you go.

878
01:25:08,880 --> 01:25:10,400
Sister-in-law, come sit here.

879
01:25:10,760 --> 01:25:12,360
You should have sat, why did you bother?

880
01:25:12,840 --> 01:25:13,840
Wait.

881
01:25:15,560 --> 01:25:16,800
My Mercan.

882
01:25:19,400 --> 01:25:19,840
Thank you.

883
01:25:20,040 --> 01:25:21,040
Enjoy.

884
01:25:23,200 --> 01:25:25,160
What’s with you two?

885
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:31,320
What’s wrong with us?

886
01:25:32,040 --> 01:25:33,120
You look too serious.

887
01:25:34,680 --> 01:25:35,800
That’s Ateş Karahan for you.

888
01:25:36,360 --> 01:25:37,999
He’s
always serious, ever since I’ve known him.

889
01:25:38,000 --> 01:25:39,000
That’s his normal state.

890
01:25:43,400 --> 01:25:45,040
It’s not like you though.

891
01:25:47,160 --> 01:25:49,560
Everything has its time and place.

892
01:25:51,520 --> 01:25:53,440
Hasn’t the time come?

893
01:25:58,200 --> 01:25:59,000
No.

894
01:25:59,200 --> 01:26:00,920
He couldn’t make it. There was traffic.

895
01:26:06,160 --> 01:26:08,200
They’re bickering so sweetly.

896
01:26:09,800 --> 01:26:11,199
Does it feel familiar?

897
01:26:11,200 --> 01:26:12,200
Of course it does.

898
01:26:14,200 --> 01:26:16,120
Are you okay?

899
01:26:19,480 --> 01:26:20,480
I’m fine.

900
01:26:22,920 --> 01:26:24,160
Today was a wonderful day.

901
01:26:24,840 --> 01:26:26,160
Because you’re with me.

902
01:26:26,600 --> 01:26:27,760
What more could I want?

903
01:26:29,080 --> 01:26:30,960
Cemal will sing us a folk song now.

904
01:26:32,000 --> 01:26:33,320
It’s my birthday today after all.

905
01:26:37,040 --> 01:26:38,040
Of course.

906
01:26:39,040 --> 01:26:40,880
Our brother was born.

907
01:26:41,680 --> 01:26:43,880
Singing a song is our duty now.

908
01:26:44,600 --> 01:26:45,600
He will sing.

909
01:26:48,920 --> 01:26:50,800
We have to sing.

910
01:26:57,120 --> 01:26:58,320
What should I sing then?

911
01:26:58,560 --> 01:26:59,800
Should I choose that too? Fine.

912
01:27:05,320 --> 01:27:08,480
Don’t wear white, it causes talk.

913
01:27:09,840 --> 01:27:12,920
Don’t wear black, it gathers dust.

914
01:27:14,800 --> 01:27:16,440
Come on everyone, don’t leave me alone.

915
01:27:17,800 --> 01:27:22,480
Let’s walk together.

916
01:27:24,280 --> 01:27:26,600
Our wish will come true quickly.

917
01:27:27,680 --> 01:27:32,040
Come swaying, come.

918
01:27:32,880 --> 01:27:37,600
Come on my dear, wander and return to me.

919
01:28:13,960 --> 01:28:14,960
Mom.

920
01:28:17,480 --> 01:28:19,880
They left you helpless, mom.

921
01:28:20,880 --> 01:28:22,240
You had no choice.

922
01:28:23,320 --> 01:28:25,319
If you had told Mrs. Nermin…

923
01:28:25,320 --> 01:28:28,560
Haydar would
have thrown you out with your two children.

924
01:28:30,760 --> 01:28:31,760
Mom.

925
01:28:34,360 --> 01:28:35,960
Being thrown out would be better.

926
01:28:37,160 --> 01:28:39,280
This man is dangerous. Everyone knows it.

927
01:28:40,000 --> 01:28:41,000
Right?

928
01:28:48,760 --> 01:28:49,760
Mom.

929
01:28:53,840 --> 01:28:56,800
You did it to protect your children, didn’t
you?

930
01:28:58,320 --> 01:29:02,400
You’ve been carrying
someone else’s sin for years, Aunt Binnaz.

931
01:29:03,320 --> 01:29:06,800
You’ve suffered.

932
01:29:11,200 --> 01:29:13,120
Haven’t you paid enough?

933
01:29:14,520 --> 01:29:16,560
If a person doesn’t forgive, God does.

934
01:29:23,360 --> 01:29:24,360
Hopefully.

935
01:29:25,640 --> 01:29:27,040
Hopefully He forgives.

936
01:29:40,080 --> 01:29:44,600
I can’t live with this shame any longer.

937
01:29:45,840 --> 01:29:46,840
Let me go.

938
01:29:47,160 --> 01:29:48,160
Let me go.

939
01:29:48,280 --> 01:29:50,960
Let me leave, let
me go back to my hometown.

940
01:29:51,600 --> 01:29:54,520
I’ll spend the rest of my life there.

941
01:30:00,840 --> 01:30:03,000
That would be better for everyone.

942
01:30:07,000 --> 01:30:10,800
No mom, please don’t go.

943
01:30:11,520 --> 01:30:12,520
Please.

944
01:30:14,320 --> 01:30:17,000
Don’t decide so suddenly. Think again.

945
01:30:23,440 --> 01:30:25,000
Please don’t go.

946
01:30:26,520 --> 01:30:28,360
Please, mom.

947
01:30:49,920 --> 01:30:52,159
How long can you run, Haydar?

948
01:30:52,160 --> 01:30:55,000
Even if you crawl into a snake’s hole…

949
01:30:55,880 --> 01:30:56,880
…I will find you.

950
01:30:58,480 --> 01:30:59,480
I will.

951
01:31:02,640 --> 01:31:04,440
I gave Demet the guest room.

952
01:31:05,080 --> 01:31:06,720
I also prepared the small room for Cemal.

953
01:31:11,720 --> 01:31:12,720
Ateş.

954
01:31:14,280 --> 01:31:15,280
Huh?

955
01:31:16,760 --> 01:31:18,400
What’s wrong, my love?

956
01:31:19,000 --> 01:31:20,720
Your mind seems somewhere else.

957
01:31:22,000 --> 01:31:23,000
It’s nothing important.

958
01:31:24,720 --> 01:31:28,640
Alright, then wait a minute.

959
01:31:29,600 --> 01:31:30,600
Where?

960
01:31:30,880 --> 01:31:31,880
Wait.

961
01:31:50,600 --> 01:31:51,600
Your birthday present.

962
01:31:52,440 --> 01:31:53,440
I made it myself.

963
01:31:55,160 --> 01:31:56,200
You didn’t have to.

964
01:31:56,520 --> 01:31:57,560
What kind of gift is it?

965
01:31:58,880 --> 01:31:59,880
Go on, open it.

966
01:32:00,120 --> 01:32:03,520
Besides, you are my most beautiful gift.

967
01:32:04,120 --> 01:32:05,440
I receive that gift every day.

968
01:32:37,920 --> 01:32:38,920
Mercan?

969
01:32:42,520 --> 01:32:43,520
Does it look like it?

970
01:32:45,280 --> 01:32:47,200
Almost identical.

971
01:32:47,920 --> 01:32:49,400
It even has the nets, look.

972
01:32:53,120 --> 01:32:54,760
How could I ever forget those nets?

973
01:33:12,480 --> 01:33:16,960
This is the most meaningful gift I’ve ever
received in my life.

974
01:33:32,640 --> 01:33:33,679
Thank you so much.

975
01:33:33,680 --> 01:33:37,840
For what you did today, and for everything…

976
01:33:39,520 --> 01:33:41,920
I’ve never felt this special in my life.

977
01:33:44,400 --> 01:33:45,400
Thank you.

978
01:33:47,720 --> 01:33:49,040
Of course you are special.

979
01:33:49,960 --> 01:33:51,440
You are my daylight.

980
01:33:57,280 --> 01:33:58,280
Come here.

981
01:34:14,160 --> 01:34:15,160
Good night.

982
01:34:29,920 --> 01:34:32,599
I just remembered our first night here…

983
01:34:32,600 --> 01:34:36,640
You shed that steel armor of yours
and showed me your romantic side here.

984
01:34:38,240 --> 01:34:40,400
With your love, you shattered my
armor to pieces.

985
01:34:41,680 --> 01:34:45,440
You
taught me how to live, how to dream again.

986
01:34:47,480 --> 01:34:48,680
I can do anything with you.

987
01:34:51,560 --> 01:34:54,079
Like this, with a backpack on our backs…

988
01:34:54,080 --> 01:34:56,800
I want us
to travel everywhere, see the whole world.

989
01:34:57,600 --> 01:35:00,240
Let there be
nowhere we haven’t seen or gone together.

990
01:35:02,320 --> 01:35:04,000
Let’s get past this wedding first.

991
01:35:05,120 --> 01:35:08,000
After that, we’ll set sail anyway.

992
01:35:09,280 --> 01:35:10,480
Let the weather warm up a bit.

993
01:35:11,200 --> 01:35:13,400
We’ll go wherever we want.

994
01:35:14,360 --> 01:35:16,200
We’ll sail into the blue waters.

995
01:35:17,240 --> 01:35:18,400
You and me.

996
01:35:18,680 --> 01:35:19,880
Just the two of us.

997
01:35:21,400 --> 01:35:22,840
We’ll anchor wherever we like.

998
01:35:24,560 --> 01:35:26,560
Wouldn’t that be beautiful?

999
01:35:30,360 --> 01:35:31,360
Mercan?

1000
01:35:40,920 --> 01:35:42,240
Come here.

1001
01:35:42,480 --> 01:35:44,920
Oh you, my tired princess.

1002
01:36:50,960 --> 01:36:52,280
Brother, Haydar has escaped.

1003
01:37:22,280 --> 01:37:23,280
Good night.

1004
01:37:24,560 --> 01:37:25,720
Sorry, are you okay?

1005
01:37:26,280 --> 01:37:28,640
What are you
doing? Why are you sneaking around quietly?

1006
01:37:28,680 --> 01:37:29,680
You scared me to death.

1007
01:37:32,080 --> 01:37:33,520
I came normally.

1008
01:37:34,320 --> 01:37:35,560
Is this your version of normal?

1009
01:37:36,680 --> 01:37:38,080
A person says something at least.

1010
01:37:38,480 --> 01:37:40,800
What kind of sound were you expecting me to
make exactly?

1011
01:37:40,880 --> 01:37:43,680
I don’t know that, but you say something.

1012
01:37:51,040 --> 01:37:52,800
What are you doing?

1013
01:37:54,240 --> 01:37:55,960
I was getting a glass.

1014
01:37:56,880 --> 01:37:59,080
And why are you here this late at night?

1015
01:37:59,520 --> 01:38:01,600
If
You allow me, I’ll drink a glass of water.

1016
01:38:04,640 --> 01:38:05,640
Alright.

1017
01:38:08,520 --> 01:38:09,800
Then I’ll go.

1018
01:38:11,080 --> 01:38:12,800
Good night.

1019
01:38:13,560 --> 01:38:14,560
Demet?

1020
01:38:17,320 --> 01:38:19,200
Yes?

1021
01:38:20,360 --> 01:38:21,680
You forgot your water.

1022
01:38:24,000 --> 01:38:25,440
Oh right.

1023
01:38:27,200 --> 01:38:28,200
That’s true.

1024
01:38:29,720 --> 01:38:30,720
Good night.

1025
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:35,000
Are you okay?

1026
01:38:45,400 --> 01:38:48,040
I’m fine, I’m fine. Thanks.

1027
01:38:49,880 --> 01:38:50,880
Good night.

1028
01:38:51,160 --> 01:38:52,160
Good night.

1029
01:39:29,400 --> 01:39:30,400
Good morning.

1030
01:39:30,960 --> 01:39:31,960
Lovebirds.

1031
01:39:33,440 --> 01:39:35,360
We came in without permission, sorry about
that.

1032
01:39:36,920 --> 01:39:37,920
Father?

1033
01:39:38,080 --> 01:39:39,080
How did you get out?

1034
01:39:40,120 --> 01:39:41,320
Nezir helped me.

1035
01:39:41,720 --> 01:39:43,800
He didn’t betray me or sell me out like you
did.

1036
01:39:47,520 --> 01:39:48,520
Ateş Karahan.

1037
01:39:56,200 --> 01:39:57,440
Ateş Karahan.

1038
01:39:58,600 --> 01:39:59,799
You took everything from me.

1039
01:39:59,800 --> 01:40:02,440
My job, my money, everything.

1040
01:40:04,520 --> 01:40:06,880
Then
you took my daughter and sent me to prison.

1041
01:40:08,400 --> 01:40:10,520
I told you your end would come by my hand.

1042
01:40:11,000 --> 01:40:12,080
Now that end has come.

1043
01:40:16,720 --> 01:40:18,240
I will send you to Eylül.

1044
01:40:20,960 --> 01:40:23,440
I set out on this path after digging my own
grave.

1045
01:40:24,040 --> 01:40:28,440
I won’t
kneel before dishonorable people like you.

1046
01:40:28,880 --> 01:40:30,479
Do whatever you want to me.

1047
01:40:30,480 --> 01:40:31,800
I don’t care.

1048
01:40:34,000 --> 01:40:35,440
Just don’t harm Mercan.

1049
01:40:37,680 --> 01:40:41,880
No. We are not that cruel.

1050
01:40:44,640 --> 01:40:45,840
Would we ever separate lovers?

1051
01:40:46,920 --> 01:40:48,600
You lived together, you will die together.

1052
01:41:05,640 --> 01:41:07,040
Mercan.

1053
01:41:18,000 --> 01:41:19,200
Mercan!

1054
01:41:20,280 --> 01:41:21,280
Ateş?

1055
01:41:25,200 --> 01:41:33,200
Thank God. Thank God.
Thank God you’re okay.

1056
01:41:33,880 --> 01:41:35,640
I’m fine.

1057
01:41:36,720 --> 01:41:37,960
Did you have a nightmare?

1058
01:41:56,480 --> 01:41:58,640
It passed.

1059
01:41:59,640 --> 01:42:00,800
You had a nightmare.

1060
01:42:01,800 --> 01:42:02,960
Something from the past.

1061
01:42:04,520 --> 01:42:06,800
Yes, it’s over. Look, I’m here with you.

1062
01:42:08,480 --> 01:42:10,400
As long as you’re with me…

1063
01:42:11,600 --> 01:42:12,600
Come on, go to sleep.

1064
01:42:13,680 --> 01:42:19,120
Come… go on, get into bed.

1065
01:42:30,280 --> 01:42:35,160
This nightmare won’t end
until Haydar and Nezir are put behind bars.

1066
01:43:01,160 --> 01:43:02,800
What’s the matter, dear bride?

1067
01:43:03,040 --> 01:43:04,640
Come, sit here.

1068
01:43:05,920 --> 01:43:07,039
What’s wrong with you?

1069
01:43:07,040 --> 01:43:08,680
What happened?

1070
01:43:09,960 --> 01:43:12,280
I’ve been feeling awful since last night,
mom.

1071
01:43:12,800 --> 01:43:14,440
Something I ate must have upset me.

1072
01:43:15,240 --> 01:43:16,320
Oh dear.

1073
01:43:16,800 --> 01:43:17,880
You look pale too.

1074
01:43:19,440 --> 01:43:21,400
Whatever you ate, we ate it too.

1075
01:43:21,760 --> 01:43:23,040
Everyone else is perfectly fine.

1076
01:43:23,640 --> 01:43:25,000
I wonder what happened to you.

1077
01:43:34,920 --> 01:43:38,959
Look at me. Could this be good news?

1078
01:43:38,960 --> 01:43:40,160
Oh my.

1079
01:43:40,360 --> 01:43:42,120
What are you talking about, mom?

1080
01:43:42,720 --> 01:43:44,280
I told you, something I ate upset me.

1081
01:43:45,080 --> 01:43:47,240
Yes, yes, what you ate
must have been blessed.

1082
01:43:49,040 --> 01:43:50,880
Of course, of course.

1083
01:43:51,560 --> 01:43:53,120
Oh my Lord.

1084
01:43:53,160 --> 01:43:55,279
After these difficult days…

1085
01:43:55,280 --> 01:43:57,360
send your servant Binnaz some good news.

1086
01:43:57,960 --> 01:44:02,120
Let me hold
my grandchild soon, God willing.

1087
01:44:03,720 --> 01:44:04,720
Look.

1088
01:44:04,800 --> 01:44:07,119
I was wondering what to
do with this blue yarn.

1089
01:44:07,120 --> 01:44:09,880
Wouldn’t it make beautiful booties?

1090
01:44:10,360 --> 01:44:10,680
Huh? Look.

1091
01:44:11,080 --> 01:44:12,440
Oh mother…

1092
01:44:14,120 --> 01:44:15,120
Mother…

1093
01:44:17,600 --> 01:44:20,159
I was thinking the same thing.

1094
01:44:20,160 --> 01:44:21,160
Did you see that?

1095
01:44:21,240 --> 01:44:22,600
Oh my dear.

1096
01:44:50,600 --> 01:44:51,960
Welcome.

1097
01:45:03,680 --> 01:45:06,880
I know my presence in
the mansion bothers you.

1098
01:45:11,200 --> 01:45:13,760
I can’t blame you for that.

1099
01:45:17,960 --> 01:45:19,800
I’ll leave as soon as my mother recovers.

1100
01:45:19,920 --> 01:45:21,320
Don’t worry.

1101
01:45:27,400 --> 01:45:28,400
We are in the study.

1102
01:45:35,040 --> 01:45:36,840
You saw it, right?

1103
01:45:37,280 --> 01:45:39,720
It’s like a completely different
Aslı in front of us.

1104
01:45:41,440 --> 01:45:42,360
You might not believe it, but…

1105
01:45:42,361 --> 01:45:44,240
she even told me about Ateş’s birthday.

1106
01:45:45,920 --> 01:45:47,600
I still think you shouldn’t trust her.

1107
01:45:48,120 --> 01:45:50,560
The
road to hell is paved with good intentions.

1108
01:45:50,880 --> 01:45:53,880
Don’t turn
your life into hell by trusting this girl.

1109
01:45:58,000 --> 01:46:00,000
Come on, let’s go.

1110
01:46:03,040 --> 01:46:03,880
You will do the planning…

1111
01:46:03,881 --> 01:46:06,560
and send the files with Burak, Ms. Zahide.

1112
01:46:07,880 --> 01:46:12,240
Alright, after I review them, I’ll
send them back to you with Burak.

1113
01:46:14,480 --> 01:46:17,200
Fine, then
we’ll set a meeting schedule accordingly.

1114
01:46:19,560 --> 01:46:23,000
Let’s also start the necessary
preparations for these transfer procedures.

1115
01:46:25,600 --> 01:46:26,600
Thank you.

1116
01:46:27,960 --> 01:46:28,960
Alright then.

1117
01:46:29,000 --> 01:46:30,160
I’m waiting for news as well.

1118
01:46:31,320 --> 01:46:32,320
What’s the situation?

1119
01:46:33,560 --> 01:46:35,120
Not much different from yesterday.

1120
01:46:36,120 --> 01:46:36,920
He was injured in prison.

1121
01:46:37,000 --> 01:46:38,200
They took him to the hospital.

1122
01:46:38,560 --> 01:46:39,720
He escaped from the hospital.

1123
01:46:42,160 --> 01:46:43,680
He couldn’t have escaped without help.

1124
01:46:46,680 --> 01:46:50,520
Maybe they staged something to escape.

1125
01:46:51,600 --> 01:46:53,920
Could Nezir be involved in this?

1126
01:46:54,200 --> 01:46:55,200
Is that what you mean?

1127
01:46:56,760 --> 01:46:57,760
I don’t know.

1128
01:46:58,680 --> 01:47:00,480
But I wouldn’t be surprised if it was him.

1129
01:47:08,440 --> 01:47:10,680
Brother, I’m
going to the company. Do you need anything?

1130
01:47:11,400 --> 01:47:13,400
Burak, Ms. Zahide will give you some files.

1131
01:47:13,480 --> 01:47:14,560
Bring them to me.

1132
01:47:15,280 --> 01:47:16,880
Alright. Anything else?

1133
01:47:17,960 --> 01:47:18,960
Yes.

1134
01:47:26,200 --> 01:47:27,560
Haydar escaped from prison.

1135
01:47:28,440 --> 01:47:29,440
What?

1136
01:47:31,120 --> 01:47:32,320
How did he escape?

1137
01:47:32,680 --> 01:47:34,520
Nothing clear yet. We don’t know either.

1138
01:47:37,360 --> 01:47:39,480
But if you’re going to the company, go with
security.

1139
01:47:44,200 --> 01:47:46,120
Alright. See you.

1140
01:48:21,880 --> 01:48:23,160
How are you now?

1141
01:48:23,800 --> 01:48:24,800
Good.

1142
01:48:24,880 --> 01:48:25,880
What is this?

1143
01:48:27,600 --> 01:48:29,040
For practice.

1144
01:48:29,880 --> 01:48:30,960
Why is Mercan the target?

1145
01:48:32,120 --> 01:48:33,120
Why did you ask?

1146
01:48:34,960 --> 01:48:37,160
There’s no need for Mercan to get hurt.

1147
01:48:38,800 --> 01:48:40,480
You didn’t use to say that before, Haydar.

1148
01:48:44,560 --> 01:48:45,920
There’s no turning back from this.

1149
01:48:46,960 --> 01:48:49,040
We’ve come too far.

1150
01:48:50,120 --> 01:48:53,800
I can’t sacrifice everyone’s
interests because of one person’s mistake.

1151
01:48:54,680 --> 01:48:55,680
What do you mean?

1152
01:48:56,360 --> 01:48:57,880
Are you going to sacrifice Mercan too?

1153
01:48:58,240 --> 01:48:59,880
Can you save her without sacrificing her?

1154
01:49:00,640 --> 01:49:01,640
Mercan wanted this.

1155
01:49:01,800 --> 01:49:04,760
No. I won’t give up on Mercan.

1156
01:49:05,400 --> 01:49:07,680
But Mercan gave up on us by going there.

1157
01:49:34,280 --> 01:49:35,520
Lower your guns.

1158
01:49:39,280 --> 01:49:41,480
What makes you think you can point a gun at
me, Haydar?

1159
01:49:43,840 --> 01:49:46,639
If you try to do business trusting
those jackals you used to work with,

1160
01:49:46,640 --> 01:49:49,760
they’ll sell you out to Ateş for pennies.

1161
01:49:52,680 --> 01:49:53,680
Good thing you have me.

1162
01:49:54,400 --> 01:49:56,320
Without me,
you are nothing, Haydar. Nothing.

1163
01:49:56,920 --> 01:49:58,240
You are nothing, Haydar. Nothing.

1164
01:50:05,360 --> 01:50:06,360
Yes.

1165
01:50:07,680 --> 01:50:09,320
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

1166
01:50:09,920 --> 01:50:12,040
This is the thrill I was looking for.

1167
01:50:19,560 --> 01:50:21,520
I have things I need to take care of.

1168
01:50:22,160 --> 01:50:23,160
It won’t take long.

1169
01:50:25,360 --> 01:50:27,000
Stay right there, Haydar.

1170
01:50:28,600 --> 01:50:29,920
You’re not going anywhere.

1171
01:50:31,200 --> 01:50:32,360
What does that mean now?

1172
01:50:33,200 --> 01:50:34,600
Am I your prisoner now too?

1173
01:50:36,680 --> 01:50:37,520
Haydar.

1174
01:50:37,521 --> 01:50:40,840
Prisoner? What kind of words are those?

1175
01:50:41,760 --> 01:50:42,920
Think of it like this.

1176
01:50:43,960 --> 01:50:45,320
A kind of visit.

1177
01:50:45,440 --> 01:50:47,280
But a mandatory visit.

1178
01:50:48,200 --> 01:50:49,320
Sit where you are.

1179
01:51:29,000 --> 01:51:30,000
Not this one.

1180
01:51:32,760 --> 01:51:33,760
This one is nice.

1181
01:51:37,240 --> 01:51:39,400
You came at just the right time, come.

1182
01:51:40,200 --> 01:51:41,200
Come, come, come.

1183
01:51:41,400 --> 01:51:43,000
I need your help.

1184
01:51:45,680 --> 01:51:46,680
At your service.

1185
01:51:46,960 --> 01:51:49,680
I’m trying to make a collage from
the photos taken on your birthday.

1186
01:51:50,280 --> 01:51:52,240
If you
have time, shall we look at them together?

1187
01:51:53,600 --> 01:51:55,280
I always have time for you.

1188
01:51:58,760 --> 01:51:59,880
Look now.

1189
01:52:03,040 --> 01:52:03,440
With this…

1190
01:52:03,880 --> 01:52:06,279
…I arranged these like this.

1191
01:52:06,280 --> 01:52:07,400
How is this?

1192
01:52:07,920 --> 01:52:08,920
Nice.

1193
01:52:09,760 --> 01:52:10,800
There are also these.

1194
01:52:15,320 --> 01:52:16,480
Like this, for example.

1195
01:52:16,680 --> 01:52:17,160
How is this?

1196
01:52:17,280 --> 01:52:18,280
That’s nice too.

1197
01:52:19,400 --> 01:52:21,160
Thanks, you’re being very helpful.

1198
01:52:23,400 --> 01:52:25,000
But they’re all beautiful, look.

1199
01:52:26,800 --> 01:52:28,280
Because you are in them.

1200
01:52:37,880 --> 01:52:39,400
Alright, alright.

1201
01:52:40,640 --> 01:52:42,160
Let’s do it like this.

1202
01:52:42,480 --> 01:52:44,840
Let’s choose the
one we started the day with first.

1203
01:52:47,360 --> 01:52:47,880
For example, this one.

1204
01:52:48,280 --> 01:52:50,400
Yes, those are marbles.

1205
01:52:54,560 --> 01:52:57,080
Look, this photo is proof that I beat you.

1206
01:52:58,920 --> 01:52:59,920
Beginner’s luck.

1207
01:53:01,120 --> 01:53:02,520
Look, this one is very nice.

1208
01:53:02,600 --> 01:53:04,720
Yes, let’s put this in the center.

1209
01:53:07,320 --> 01:53:08,320
Like this.

1210
01:53:16,080 --> 01:53:17,640
Look, this one is also very nice.

1211
01:53:18,840 --> 01:53:21,240
Just you and me against the Istanbul view.

1212
01:53:22,320 --> 01:53:24,240
My most beautiful view is you.

1213
01:53:26,520 --> 01:53:27,600
Let’s include this one too.

1214
01:53:27,920 --> 01:53:29,160
Let’s place this one here.

1215
01:53:33,120 --> 01:53:34,320
These turned out very nice.

1216
01:53:35,840 --> 01:53:37,360
Because that’s who we are.

1217
01:53:38,960 --> 01:53:40,479
Some moments end, but…

1218
01:53:40,480 --> 01:53:42,720
…their memory lasts a lifetime.

1219
01:53:44,280 --> 01:53:45,960
Today was exactly like that.

1220
01:53:49,080 --> 01:53:51,840
You wish you could stay in those moments a
little longer.

1221
01:53:53,600 --> 01:53:54,600
We’ll do it again.

1222
01:53:57,160 --> 01:53:58,160
Alright.

1223
01:53:58,560 --> 01:54:00,520
Now we need to get these framed.

1224
01:54:00,560 --> 01:54:01,240
I’ll hang them on the wall.

1225
01:54:01,241 --> 01:54:02,520
Okay.

1226
01:54:02,680 --> 01:54:04,480
But don’t mix up the order.

1227
01:54:04,680 --> 01:54:05,680
It should be like this.

1228
01:54:06,000 --> 01:54:08,880
Okay, I’ll give them
to the guys now, they’ll take them.

1229
01:54:10,920 --> 01:54:13,120
But they should be quick. It will
look great.

1230
01:54:13,640 --> 01:54:15,040
Alright, I’ll give them right away.

1231
01:55:09,720 --> 01:55:11,640
Forgive me, my son!

1232
01:55:13,240 --> 01:55:15,080
Forgive me, my child!

1233
01:55:17,640 --> 01:55:20,240
Forgive me, my Murat.

1234
01:55:25,760 --> 01:55:29,440
That scoundrel lied to us.

1235
01:55:30,200 --> 01:55:32,400
He turned us against each other.

1236
01:55:35,280 --> 01:55:37,400
If I had known…

1237
01:55:38,480 --> 01:55:39,920
If I had known…

1238
01:55:40,160 --> 01:55:43,200
I would have wrapped you in cotton and held
you close.

1239
01:55:43,400 --> 01:55:44,400
Murat!

1240
01:55:47,960 --> 01:55:49,240
If I had known.

1241
01:55:49,640 --> 01:55:52,280
My son, if I had known, forgive me, please.

1242
01:55:55,480 --> 01:55:56,760
I couldn’t even smell you.

1243
01:55:58,000 --> 01:56:00,600
I couldn’t hold you even once.

1244
01:56:01,680 --> 01:56:02,680
Murat!

1245
01:56:13,680 --> 01:56:16,200
How dare you come here?

1246
01:56:18,440 --> 01:56:20,680
With what face?

1247
01:56:24,720 --> 01:56:29,400
Instead of embracing your son, now
you embrace the soil.

1248
01:56:34,440 --> 01:56:37,360
You made me suffer so much.

1249
01:56:38,120 --> 01:56:39,680
God did not accept this.

1250
01:56:45,280 --> 01:56:46,520
He reversed fate.

1251
01:56:49,000 --> 01:56:52,239
From now on, you
will be known as a child killer.

1252
01:56:52,240 --> 01:56:55,960
Your heart will burn with this pain.

1253
01:56:58,480 --> 01:56:59,800
Shut up and get out.

1254
01:57:04,520 --> 01:57:05,520
Get out.

1255
01:57:07,080 --> 01:57:09,400
You brought this upon yourself.

1256
01:57:10,400 --> 01:57:11,920
You made all of us suffer.

1257
01:57:12,640 --> 01:57:14,440
I said go, leave me alone with my son.

1258
01:57:15,960 --> 01:57:16,960
Your son?

1259
01:57:18,840 --> 01:57:20,639
I raised him.

1260
01:57:20,640 --> 01:57:22,640
I held him close.

1261
01:57:24,120 --> 01:57:26,280
I was there when he had a fever.

1262
01:57:28,360 --> 01:57:30,160
He shared his joy with me.

1263
01:57:32,880 --> 01:57:34,160
You cannot be a mother.

1264
01:57:39,520 --> 01:57:41,560
You only gave birth to him.

1265
01:57:42,920 --> 01:57:44,120
Then you killed him.

1266
01:57:46,720 --> 01:57:47,800
Get out of here.

1267
01:57:50,760 --> 01:57:52,960
You are condemned to live with this pain.

1268
01:57:56,280 --> 01:58:02,440
If I knew I was a child
killer, I would take my own life.

1269
01:58:04,240 --> 01:58:05,240
I said get out.

1270
01:58:05,480 --> 01:58:06,560
Get out.

1271
01:58:11,640 --> 01:58:13,200
I wish you had some honor.

1272
01:58:38,080 --> 01:58:40,600
My son died because of you.

1273
01:58:44,120 --> 01:58:45,400
I will kill all of you.

1274
01:58:45,920 --> 01:58:47,520
I will make you suffer worse than death.

1275
01:58:50,360 --> 01:58:52,480
I will start with Haydar Yıldırım.

1276
01:58:52,760 --> 01:58:54,039
Because he is the head of the snake.

1277
01:58:54,040 --> 01:58:58,240
Then it will be your turn, one by one.

1278
01:59:02,400 --> 01:59:03,560
I promise you, my son.

1279
01:59:04,040 --> 01:59:08,440
When I’m done with the
Yıldırıms, I will come to you too.

1280
01:59:09,760 --> 01:59:11,560
I will come to you too.

1281
01:59:11,960 --> 01:59:13,640
I will come, my mother.

1282
01:59:14,320 --> 01:59:15,760
I will come, my child.

1283
02:00:15,760 --> 02:00:17,320
Leave the jacket.

1284
02:00:18,240 --> 02:00:19,480
He is already here.

1285
02:00:44,640 --> 02:00:45,640
Why are we doing this?

1286
02:00:46,240 --> 02:00:47,240
A rehearsal.

1287
02:00:47,560 --> 02:00:50,200
I want everything to be
perfect on the dance floor at the wedding.

1288
02:00:50,520 --> 02:00:51,040
Don’t worry.

1289
02:00:51,440 --> 02:00:52,720
Everything will be as you want.

1290
02:00:54,600 --> 02:00:55,880
What did you do with the photos?

1291
02:00:56,200 --> 02:00:57,200
I had them done.

1292
02:00:57,240 --> 02:00:58,000
They will be on your wall today.

1293
02:00:58,001 --> 02:00:59,520
That was fast.

1294
02:01:00,880 --> 02:01:02,480
When the order comes from you…

1295
02:01:09,680 --> 02:01:11,960
You are so beautiful…

1296
02:01:13,520 --> 02:01:15,200
You take my breath away.

1297
02:01:17,200 --> 02:01:18,960
I’ve started to fear making mistakes.

1298
02:01:20,280 --> 02:01:22,320
I think we should keep our heads clear for
a while.

1299
02:01:23,640 --> 02:01:25,280
However it will be…

1300
02:01:25,920 --> 02:01:28,360
Good thing you have a reliable bridesmaid.

1301
02:01:28,640 --> 02:01:29,640
And I have my best man.

1302
02:01:34,280 --> 02:01:35,840
Did I step on your foot?

1303
02:01:36,800 --> 02:01:37,960
That’s not stepping.

1304
02:01:38,320 --> 02:01:39,520
You clearly applied force.

1305
02:01:40,520 --> 02:01:41,520
Come on now.

1306
02:01:48,800 --> 02:01:49,960
If it’s love, then let it be.

1307
02:01:53,480 --> 02:01:55,920
But what if your
delicate feet get hurt afterward?

1308
02:01:56,960 --> 02:01:57,960
They won’t.

1309
02:01:58,920 --> 02:02:00,520
Then I can step on them again.

1310
02:02:07,160 --> 02:02:09,680
You can step on them as much as you want.

1311
02:02:15,240 --> 02:02:17,280
I think the music ended.

1312
02:02:19,360 --> 02:02:20,160
Well…

1313
02:02:20,161 --> 02:02:21,601
We haven’t looked at the shirts yet.

1314
02:02:22,040 --> 02:02:23,200
You can check those.

1315
02:02:23,600 --> 02:02:25,400
No, but they sent the photos.

1316
02:02:25,480 --> 02:02:26,616
They’re waiting for our response.

1317
02:02:26,640 --> 02:02:29,120
You’ll decide anyway, you can check them.

1318
02:02:29,720 --> 02:02:31,080
No, we’ll check them together.

1319
02:02:35,960 --> 02:02:42,720
[Malik speaks Arabic]

1320
02:02:44,880 --> 02:02:46,760
[Malik’s mother speaks Arabic]

1321
02:02:48,360 --> 02:02:49,080
I…

1322
02:02:49,081 --> 02:02:51,400
I did everything for your good.

1323
02:02:52,560 --> 02:02:53,280
Please…

1324
02:02:53,281 --> 02:02:55,600
Please don’t doubt my good intentions.

1325
02:02:56,400 --> 02:02:58,320
You’re still talking about good intentions,
mom.

1326
02:02:59,080 --> 02:03:01,056
You’re
doing something wrong with good intentions.

1327
02:03:01,080 --> 02:03:03,079
My father and you…

1328
02:03:03,080 --> 02:03:05,360
Stop thinking everyone is bad.

1329
02:03:05,880 --> 02:03:06,680
I…

1330
02:03:06,681 --> 02:03:09,199
I only wanted to protect my son…

1331
02:03:09,200 --> 02:03:11,680
from selfish people.

1332
02:03:16,840 --> 02:03:18,120
You say selfish.

1333
02:03:20,120 --> 02:03:21,320
Mom, Çiçek is not selfish.

1334
02:03:22,720 --> 02:03:24,320
I’ve told you this many times.

1335
02:03:25,080 --> 02:03:26,976
I told you not
to interfere in our relationship.

1336
02:03:27,000 --> 02:03:28,000
But what did you do?

1337
02:03:28,440 --> 02:03:29,999
You went ahead and did
what you wanted again.

1338
02:03:30,000 --> 02:03:32,520
You forced
that poor girl into a prenuptial agreement.

1339
02:03:35,680 --> 02:03:36,880
[Malik’s mother speaks Arabic]

1340
02:03:37,080 --> 02:03:39,000
People change.

1341
02:03:40,000 --> 02:03:40,760
At first…

1342
02:03:40,761 --> 02:03:42,480
they seem like angels.

1343
02:03:43,520 --> 02:03:45,879
When things go bad…

1344
02:03:45,880 --> 02:03:47,280
they turn into devils.

1345
02:03:50,480 --> 02:03:52,960
This applies to Çiçek as well.

1346
02:03:54,040 --> 02:03:55,040
No.

1347
02:03:55,840 --> 02:03:57,239
Whatever I say to you…

1348
02:03:57,240 --> 02:03:58,240
whatever I tell you…

1349
02:03:59,000 --> 02:04:00,000
it’s pointless.

1350
02:04:00,840 --> 02:04:02,240
So I’m not saying anything anymore.

1351
02:04:03,200 --> 02:04:04,720
I don’t need your protection.

1352
02:04:05,840 --> 02:04:07,280
I don’t want your money.

1353
02:04:09,560 --> 02:04:10,936
I don’t want to see either of you...

1354
02:04:10,960 --> 02:04:12,080
anymore.

1355
02:04:40,560 --> 02:04:41,760
Malik, don’t go.

1356
02:04:53,000 --> 02:04:55,199
I did everything...

1357
02:04:55,200 --> 02:04:58,120
because I love you so much.

1358
02:05:03,080 --> 02:05:04,440
Oh, Malik.

1359
02:05:04,920 --> 02:05:06,400
Don’t you feel sorry for your mother?

1360
02:05:09,800 --> 02:05:10,800
Snake.

1361
02:05:12,520 --> 02:05:14,160
You dare mock my pain?

1362
02:05:16,160 --> 02:05:18,240
I’ll make you regret being born.

1363
02:05:18,360 --> 02:05:20,280
You’ll crawl in the streets.

1364
02:05:26,960 --> 02:05:30,200
You
won’t escape my wrath either, little snake.

1365
02:05:33,280 --> 02:05:35,640
You seduced Ateş
and made him give up on revenge.

1366
02:05:35,840 --> 02:05:37,960
You’ll pay for that too.

1367
02:05:48,520 --> 02:05:50,120
You...

1368
02:05:53,760 --> 02:05:54,960
Haydar Yıldırım...

1369
02:05:55,840 --> 02:06:00,720
The one responsible for all my suffering...

1370
02:06:00,880 --> 02:06:04,040
You took my child, you
made me a murderer of my own child.

1371
02:06:05,040 --> 02:06:07,280
I’ll kill you with my own hands.

1372
02:06:10,800 --> 02:06:12,640
I’ll kill you.

1373
02:06:14,720 --> 02:06:16,360
I’ll kill you with my own hands.

1374
02:06:17,200 --> 02:06:18,920
I’ll kill you, Haydar.

1375
02:06:21,080 --> 02:06:24,200
I’ll kill you, I’ll kill you, I’ll kill
you.

1376
02:06:24,840 --> 02:06:27,040
Mom, mom, what are you doing?

1377
02:06:27,840 --> 02:06:29,560
Mom, come sit here.

1378
02:06:29,960 --> 02:06:31,680
Mom, please don’t, come.

1379
02:06:32,040 --> 02:06:34,839
Come, I’m scared something will happen to
you, please.

1380
02:06:34,840 --> 02:06:38,400
Do you think I care what happens to me?

1381
02:06:38,520 --> 02:06:42,040
I sent my own child to
death with my own hands.

1382
02:06:42,960 --> 02:06:45,400
I became the angel of death for my child.

1383
02:06:47,400 --> 02:06:49,840
Mom, how could you have known?

1384
02:06:50,200 --> 02:06:51,200
Don’t blame yourself.

1385
02:07:05,600 --> 02:07:07,760
Hello?

1386
02:07:11,560 --> 02:07:14,000
What? He escaped from the hospital?

1387
02:07:14,960 --> 02:07:15,960
Where is he?

1388
02:07:18,960 --> 02:07:20,520
Search everywhere, find him.

1389
02:07:21,360 --> 02:07:26,080
Find Haydar before Ateş does. If he finds
him, he’ll send him straight to prison.

1390
02:07:27,080 --> 02:07:32,160
I’ll give you whatever
money you want. Just bring me Haydar. Now!

1391
02:07:38,880 --> 02:07:39,880
What happened, Mom?

1392
02:07:41,800 --> 02:07:43,400
I’ll kill you, Haydar.

1393
02:07:44,920 --> 02:07:46,160
Mom, what did you do?

1394
02:07:48,960 --> 02:07:49,960
What had to be done.

1395
02:07:59,440 --> 02:08:05,200
I think the first one we
looked at was better. Come, look, this one.

1396
02:08:06,800 --> 02:08:08,000
Let me see.

1397
02:08:10,720 --> 02:08:11,720
It’s nice, yeah.

1398
02:08:17,040 --> 02:08:18,520
I know you’re brushing it off.

1399
02:08:21,080 --> 02:08:22,120
But fine.

1400
02:08:23,440 --> 02:08:28,959
We handled the shirt.
Maybe we should decide on the hair too?

1401
02:08:28,960 --> 02:08:31,000
What’s wrong with my hair?

1402
02:08:32,880 --> 02:08:37,360
I
Mean, maybe we could try a different style.

1403
02:08:38,240 --> 02:08:41,000
Thanks, but everyone already likes my hair
like this.

1404
02:08:41,680 --> 02:08:44,040
Excuse me? Who likes you like this?

1405
02:08:46,240 --> 02:08:47,760
I mean... everyone.

1406
02:08:48,640 --> 02:08:52,480
Alright, I see. Then
let the people who like you decide.

1407
02:08:53,280 --> 02:08:54,960
I’m kidding, I’m kidding, come here.

1408
02:08:55,880 --> 02:08:56,880
You get upset so quickly.

1409
02:09:02,760 --> 02:09:10,759
Good thing I
know you’re joking. Otherwise...

1410
02:09:10,760 --> 02:09:13,640
Seeing you smile like this is so beautiful.

1411
02:09:16,600 --> 02:09:18,480
I know you’ve been upset since yesterday.

1412
02:09:20,120 --> 02:09:21,560
You’re trying not to show it to me.

1413
02:09:22,480 --> 02:09:25,320
So I won’t get upset too, but...

1414
02:09:29,600 --> 02:09:32,800
I am upset, yes, but I’m handling it.

1415
02:09:35,880 --> 02:09:37,280
Don’t think about these things now.

1416
02:09:37,720 --> 02:09:38,720
Focus on the wedding.

1417
02:09:39,720 --> 02:09:42,840
Look, my shirt, my
hair, everything is in your hands.

1418
02:09:44,280 --> 02:09:45,280
Okay.

1419
02:09:45,760 --> 02:09:46,920
But you should know this too.

1420
02:09:47,800 --> 02:09:49,680
I’m always ready to listen to you.

1421
02:09:51,280 --> 02:09:54,399
And I
don’t want a frowning groom at the wedding.

1422
02:09:54,400 --> 02:09:58,400
Smile more like this.
Always smile like this.

1423
02:10:03,480 --> 02:10:04,480
Hello?

1424
02:10:08,720 --> 02:10:09,760
Okay, thank you.

1425
02:10:12,600 --> 02:10:13,600
What happened?

1426
02:10:14,680 --> 02:10:18,720
I had started the process to open an organ
transplant department at Eylül Hospital.

1427
02:10:19,960 --> 02:10:22,520
They just said everything
is ready to get the permits.

1428
02:10:30,080 --> 02:10:34,080
You are an unbelievably kind person.

1429
02:10:45,480 --> 02:10:47,600
Sorry, I think I came at a bad time.

1430
02:10:48,040 --> 02:10:50,600
No, wait, Cemal. I was just leaving anyway.

1431
02:10:51,600 --> 02:10:52,600
Go ahead.

1432
02:10:52,840 --> 02:10:54,600
I could have come later.

1433
02:10:59,080 --> 02:11:00,080
What happened?

1434
02:11:00,880 --> 02:11:01,600
Is there bad news?

1435
02:11:01,840 --> 02:11:03,160
Things got pretty complicated.

1436
02:11:04,240 --> 02:11:05,759
Haydar was stabbed and
taken to the hospital.

1437
02:11:05,760 --> 02:11:08,760
I asked around, but it’s off the record.

1438
02:11:10,000 --> 02:11:12,160
The one who did it was hired for money.

1439
02:11:12,680 --> 02:11:14,960
And he’s from Adana. That’s all we have.

1440
02:11:27,840 --> 02:11:28,840
Mom.

1441
02:11:38,120 --> 02:11:39,120
What happened here?

1442
02:11:43,760 --> 02:11:45,199
She had a breakdown.

1443
02:11:45,200 --> 02:11:48,000
She tore up everything
she could get her hands on.

1444
02:11:55,960 --> 02:11:57,120
Look, Müzeyyen.

1445
02:11:58,120 --> 02:11:59,120
I understand your pain.

1446
02:12:01,960 --> 02:12:03,360
But you’re doing the wrong things.

1447
02:12:06,160 --> 02:12:07,600
You had Haydar stabbed, didn’t you?

1448
02:12:11,680 --> 02:12:14,200
Yes. I did.

1449
02:12:14,800 --> 02:12:16,640
I’m loyal to the oath I made.

1450
02:12:17,040 --> 02:12:18,960
I didn’t give up on revenge like you did.

1451
02:12:20,160 --> 02:12:22,000
Our revenge had already been taken.

1452
02:12:23,000 --> 02:12:26,320
If you had stayed
calm, Haydar would be in prison right now.

1453
02:12:26,760 --> 02:12:28,640
Do you know where I just came from?

1454
02:12:29,920 --> 02:12:31,360
From my son’s grave.

1455
02:12:38,640 --> 02:12:40,200
His soil is still on my hands.

1456
02:12:46,920 --> 02:12:49,920
Without knowing, I stained my hands
with blood.

1457
02:12:50,440 --> 02:12:52,000
Even if I wash them, it won’t come off.

1458
02:12:59,680 --> 02:13:02,520
I’m in such deep pain, my heart is burning.

1459
02:13:04,720 --> 02:13:07,520
That man made me a killer of my own child.

1460
02:13:13,680 --> 02:13:15,360
It’s my duty to punish him.

1461
02:13:19,960 --> 02:13:24,240
He escaped my hands this time, that
bastard, but I’ll chase him until he dies.

1462
02:13:33,320 --> 02:13:33,520
Mom.

1463
02:13:34,040 --> 02:13:35,040
Come, sit.

1464
02:13:36,240 --> 02:13:37,240
Come.

1465
02:13:39,240 --> 02:13:40,240
Oh, Müzeyyen.

1466
02:13:41,200 --> 02:13:42,800
We said we are not killers.

1467
02:13:43,360 --> 02:13:45,160
Besides, he was already
serving his sentence.

1468
02:13:47,800 --> 02:13:49,440
Death would be a release for Haydar.

1469
02:13:50,560 --> 02:13:53,640
He should suffer his punishment for
the rest of his life.

1470
02:13:55,080 --> 02:13:56,080
That’s what’s right.

1471
02:13:57,160 --> 02:13:58,480
Control your anger now.

1472
02:13:59,680 --> 02:14:00,680
Ateş is right, Mom.

1473
02:14:03,120 --> 02:14:04,560
Don’t let your anger take over.

1474
02:14:06,200 --> 02:14:09,280
I know because I made
the same mistake before.

1475
02:14:19,440 --> 02:14:23,200
That fire inside me won’t go out until that
man is dead.

1476
02:14:24,640 --> 02:14:25,640
It won’t go out.

1477
02:14:27,200 --> 02:14:29,600
Stop now, Müzeyyen.

1478
02:14:31,000 --> 02:14:35,760
Stop before
you hurt yourself and us any further.

1479
02:15:00,880 --> 02:15:01,880
It will pass.

1480
02:15:04,120 --> 02:15:05,120
It will pass.

1481
02:15:23,080 --> 02:15:24,560
Did you cut your hand?

1482
02:15:24,960 --> 02:15:25,960
Wait.

1483
02:15:33,120 --> 02:15:34,600
Oh, Malik, sit down.

1484
02:15:35,240 --> 02:15:35,920
Will you sit?

1485
02:15:36,040 --> 02:15:37,119
No, it’s nothing serious.

1486
02:15:37,120 --> 02:15:38,120
Sit.

1487
02:15:43,040 --> 02:15:44,640
Oh, Malik.

1488
02:15:48,680 --> 02:15:54,360
When you act out of anger like this, you
hurt both yourself and the other person.

1489
02:15:57,000 --> 02:15:57,720
What do you mean?

1490
02:15:57,920 --> 02:15:58,920
I don’t understand.

1491
02:15:59,920 --> 02:16:02,080
I heard you talking to your mother.

1492
02:16:03,440 --> 02:16:08,040
I waited for you to calm down before coming
to you, but you’re still furious.

1493
02:16:12,040 --> 02:16:13,440
How can I stay calm?

1494
02:16:13,880 --> 02:16:15,200
You have to, Malik.

1495
02:16:16,040 --> 02:16:17,360
She’s your mother.

1496
02:16:17,560 --> 02:16:18,840
The woman who gave birth to you.

1497
02:16:20,080 --> 02:16:21,960
You can’t turn your back on your mother.

1498
02:16:24,440 --> 02:16:26,200
She tried to separate us, Çiçek.

1499
02:16:27,120 --> 02:16:30,160
Even though I objected
so much, she still did what she wanted.

1500
02:16:30,280 --> 02:16:32,240
She came and forced you
into a marriage contract.

1501
02:16:42,440 --> 02:16:46,600
When my mother opposed
us, you told me not to turn my back on her.

1502
02:16:48,000 --> 02:16:50,160
Now I’m telling you the same thing.

1503
02:16:54,480 --> 02:16:58,120
Just like my mother
accepted our relationship, yours will too.

1504
02:17:00,760 --> 02:17:03,480
The only thing we need to do is be patient.

1505
02:17:04,280 --> 02:17:06,640
Win their consent, win their hearts.

1506
02:17:21,760 --> 02:17:23,400
I wish my mother knew you too.

1507
02:17:24,040 --> 02:17:25,240
Saw your beautiful heart.

1508
02:17:27,440 --> 02:17:29,960
No matter what, everything has its time.

1509
02:17:30,680 --> 02:17:31,920
But promise me.

1510
02:17:32,720 --> 02:17:35,800
From now on, you’ll be more understanding
toward your mother, okay?

1511
02:17:38,000 --> 02:17:39,000
Okay.

1512
02:17:40,600 --> 02:17:43,000
I’ll try to do as you say.

1513
02:18:02,480 --> 02:18:06,280
We’re not only dealing with our enemies.
We’re also dealing with our families.

1514
02:18:08,320 --> 02:18:09,520
Alright, brother, don’t worry.

1515
02:18:10,040 --> 02:18:12,640
Sooner or later, we’ll
get through this with our heads held high.

1516
02:18:13,160 --> 02:18:15,360
We will, but when, how?

1517
02:18:15,600 --> 02:18:18,119
They’re still
nowhere to be found. Both Haydar and Nezir.

1518
02:18:18,120 --> 02:18:20,320
It’s like the ground swallowed them whole.

1519
02:18:24,800 --> 02:18:26,280
They might be setting something up.

1520
02:18:26,720 --> 02:18:27,760
We need to be careful.

1521
02:18:35,720 --> 02:18:36,720
Hello.

1522
02:18:38,520 --> 02:18:39,520
Hello, it’s me, Haydar.

1523
02:18:42,760 --> 02:18:44,640
You finally showed up.

1524
02:18:48,800 --> 02:18:50,680
I hear you’ve
been searching for me everywhere.

1525
02:18:51,960 --> 02:18:54,160
You
started a war you’re going to lose, Haydar.

1526
02:18:56,160 --> 02:18:59,080
You might be
walking around freely right now.

1527
02:18:59,920 --> 02:19:03,440
But soon, I’ll send you back to that hole
you crawled out of.

1528
02:19:04,760 --> 02:19:06,800
You won’t put me back in that hole.

1529
02:19:09,160 --> 02:19:11,480
But I’ll bury you underground.

1530
02:19:11,800 --> 02:19:13,280
You’re chasing empty dreams.

1531
02:19:14,280 --> 02:19:15,600
You and Nezir.

1532
02:19:16,760 --> 02:19:17,760
Nezir.

1533
02:19:18,680 --> 02:19:20,680
Are you listening to me
from there like a coward?

1534
02:19:21,120 --> 02:19:23,360
You should have killed me when you had the
chance, Ateş.

1535
02:19:30,400 --> 02:19:32,400
But I won’t show you mercy.

1536
02:19:40,400 --> 02:19:41,600
Who said anything about mercy?

1537
02:19:42,240 --> 02:19:44,360
You’re not even worth dirtying my hands.

1538
02:19:44,720 --> 02:19:46,400
The police are looking for you everywhere.

1539
02:19:46,640 --> 02:19:47,640
And so am I.

1540
02:19:53,960 --> 02:19:59,600
If you have any sense, both you and Haydar
will turn yourselves in.

1541
02:20:00,440 --> 02:20:02,840
No one can send me back to that prison.

1542
02:20:03,360 --> 02:20:04,360
No one!

1543
02:20:19,600 --> 02:20:22,720
Enjoy your life, Ateş.

1544
02:20:23,200 --> 02:20:24,560
Because the countdown has started.
